Program to find square of a number

No Return Type, No Arguments / Parameters

CODE
'''
Purpose of Program
The main purpose of this Python Program is to demonstrate how we can use Functions to calculate square of a number and
display it on the Output Screen. Please note that the Function Prototype will be: No Return Type, No Arguments / Parameters
This program comprises of two Functions.
1. main()
2. square_calculation()
'''

# Function Prototypes for User Defined Functions
# void square_calculation(); # Function Prototype
def square_calculation():
    try:
# Input
# Variable to store Input - number
# Variable to store Output - square
        number = float(input("Enter a Number: "))
# Processing + Output
        square = number * number
# Display Input and Output
        print("Entered Number is",number)
        print(f"Square of {number} is {square}")
    except ValueError:
        print("Error! Enter Integer Value")
if __name__ == "__main__": # main() Function
    square_calculation() # Function Call

Enter a Number:  11

Entered Number is 11.0
Square of 11.0 is 121.0

No Return Type, Arguments / Parameters

CODE
'''
Purpose of Program
The main purpose of this Python Program is to demonstrate how we can use Functions to calculate square of a number and display it on the Output Screen. Please note that the Function Prototype will be: No Return Type, Arguments / Parameters
This program comprises of two Functions.
1. main()
2. square_calculation()
'''

# Function Prototypes for User Defined Functions
# void square_calculation(number); # Function Prototype
def square_calculation(number):
    # Processing + Output
        square = number * number
# Display Input and Output
        print("Entered Number is",number)
        print(f"Square of {number} is {square}")
    
if __name__ == "__main__": # main() Function
    try:
# Input
# Variable to store Input - number
# Variable to store Output - square
        number = float(input("Enter a Number: "))
        square_calculation(number) # Function Call
    except ValueError:
        print("Error! Enter Integer/Float Value")
Enter a Number:  11

Entered Number is 11.0
Square of 11.0 is 121.0

Program to add two float number

No Return Type, No Arguments / Parameters

CODE
'''
Purpose of Program
The main purpose of this Python Program is to demonstrate how we can use Functions to calculate sum of two float numbers and
display it on the Output Screen. Please note that the Function Prototype will be: No Return Type, No Arguments / Parameters
This program comprises of two Functions.
1. main()
2. float_addition()
'''

# Function Prototypes for User Defined Functions
# void grade_calculation1(); # Function Prototype
def float_addition():
    try:
# Input
# Variable to store Input - number1, number2
# Variable to store Output - sum
        number1 = float(input("Enter First Number: "))
        number2 = float(input("Enter Second Number: "))
# Processing + Output
        sum = number1 + number2
# Display Input and Output
        print("First Entered Number is ",number1)
        print("Second Entered Number is ",number2)
        print(f"Sum of {number1} and {number2} is {sum} ")
    except ValueError:
        print("Error! Enter Integer/Float Value")
if __name__ == "__main__": # main() Function
    float_addition() # Function Call
Enter First Number:  3.5
Enter Second Number:  3

First Entered Number is:  3.5
Second Entered Number is:  3.0
Sum of 3.5 and 3.0 is 6.5

No Return Type, Arguments / Parameters

CODE
'''
Purpose of Program
The main purpose of this Python Program is to demonstrate how we can use Functions to calculate sum of two float numbers and
display it on the Output Screen. Please note that the Function Prototype will be: No Return Type, No Arguments / Parameters
This program comprises of two Functions.
1. main()
2. float_addition()
'''

# Function Prototypes for User Defined Functions
# void grade_calculation1(); # Function Prototype
def float_addition(number1,number2):
    # Processing + Output
        sum = number1 + number2
# Display Input and Output
        print("First Entered Number is ",number1)
        print("Second Entered Number is ",number2)
        print(f"Sum of {number1} and {number2} is {sum} ")

if __name__ == "__main__": # main() Function
    try:
# Input
# Variable to store Input - number1, number2
# Variable to store Output - sum
        number1 = float(input("Enter First Number: "))
        number2 = float(input("Enter Second Number: "))
        float_addition(number1,number2) # Function Call
    except ValueError:
        print("Error! Enter Integer/Float Value")
Enter First Number:  3.5
Enter Second Number:  6.5

First Entered Number is  3.5
Second Entered Number is  6.5
Sum of 3.5 and 6.5 is 10.0

Program to check if it is an even number or odd number?

No Return Type, No Arguments / Parameters

CODE
'''
Purpose of Program
The main purpose of this Python Program is to demonstrate how we can use Functions to calculate if a number is even or odd and
display it on the Output Screen. Please note that the Function Prototype will be: No Return Type, No Arguments / Parameters
This program comprises of two Functions.
1. main()
2. check_even_odd()
'''

# Function Prototypes for User Defined Functions
# void even_odd_calculation(); # Function Prototype
def check_even_odd():
    try:
# Input
# Variable to store Input - number
# Variable to store Output - N/A
        number = int(input("Enter a Number: "))
# Processing + Output
        if number % 2 == 0:
            print(f"{number} is an Even Number")
        elif number % 2 != 0:
            print(f"{number} is an Odd Number")
    except ValueError:
        print("Error! Enter Integer/Float Value")
if __name__ == "__main__": # main() Function
    check_even_odd() # Function Call
Enter a Number:  3

3 is an Odd Number

Program to find square of a number

Return Type, No Arguments / Parameters

CODE
'''
Purpose of Program
The main purpose of this Python Program is to demonstrate how we can use Functions to calculate grade of a student in Math and display it on the Output Screen. Please note that the Function Prototype will be: Return Type, No Arguments / Parameters
This program comprises of two Functions.
1. main()
2. square_calculation()
'''

# Function Prototypes for User Defined Functions
# string square_calculation(); # Function Prototype
def square_calculation():
    try:
# Input
# Variable to store Input - number
# Variable to store Output - square
        number = float(input("Enter a Number: "))
# Processing + Output
        square = number * number
# RETRUN result (Output) to the Calling Function
        return square
    except ValueError:
        print("Error! Enter Integer/Float Value")
if __name__ == "__main__": # main() Function
# When a function returns a value, use Assignment Statement ot Call Function
    result = square_calculation() # Function Call
# Display Input and Output
    print("Entered Number is",number)
    print(f"Square of {number} is {result}")
Enter a Number:  11

Entered Number is 11.0
Square of 11.0 is 121.0

Return Type, Arguments / Parameters

CODE
'''
Purpose of Program
The main purpose of this Python Program is to demonstrate how we can use Functions to calculate square of a number and display it on the Output Screen. Please note that the Function Prototype will be: Return Type, Arguments / Parameters
This program comprises of two Functions.
1. main()
2. square_calculation()
'''

# Function Prototypes for User Defined Functions
# string square_calculation(number); # Function Prototype
def square_calculation(number):
    # Processing + Output
        square = number * number
# RETRUN result (Output) to the Calling Function
        return square
    
if __name__ == "__main__": # main() Function
    try:
# Input
# Variable to store Input - number
# Variable to store Output - square
        number = float(input("Enter a Number: "))
        result = square_calculation(number) # Function Call
# Display Input and Output
        print("Entered Number is",number)
        print(f"Square of {number} is {result}")
    except ValueError:
        print("Error! Enter Integer/Float Value")
Enter a Number:  11

Entered Number is 11.0
Square of 11.0 is 121.0

Return Type, No Arguments / Parameters

CODE
'''
Purpose of Program
The main purpose of this Python Program is to demonstrate how we can use Functions to calculate sum of two float numbers and

This program comprises of two Functions.

2. float_addition()
'''

# Function Prototypes for User Defined Functions
# string float_addition(); # Function Prototype
def float_addition():
    try:
# Input
# Variable to store Input - number1, number2
# Variable to store Output - sum
        number1 = float(input("Enter First Number: "))
        number2 = float(input("Enter Second Number: "))
# Processing + Output
        sum = number1 + number2
# RETRUN result (Output) to the Calling Function
        return sum
    except ValueError:
        print("Error! Enter Integer/Float Value")
if __name__ == "__main__": # main() Function
# When a function returns a value, use Assignment Statement ot Call Function
    result = float_addition() # Function Call
    # Display Input and Output
    print("First Entered Number is ",number1)
    print("Second Entered Number is ",number2)
    print(f"Sum of {number1} and {number2} is {result} ")

CODE
'''
Purpose of Program
The main purpose of this Python Program is to demonstrate how we can use Functions to calculate sum of two float numbers and
display it on the Output Screen. Please note that the Function Prototype will be: No Return Type, Arguments / Parameters
This program comprises of two Functions.
1. main()
2. float_addition()
'''

# Function Prototypes for User Defined Functions
# void float_addition(); # Function Prototype
def float_addition(number1,number2):
    # Processing + Output
        sum = number1 + number2
# RETRUN result (Output) to the Calling Function
        return sum


if __name__ == "__main__": # main() Function
    try:
# Input
# Variable to store Input - number1, number2
# Variable to store Output - sum
        number1 = float(input("Enter First Number: "))
        number2 = float(input("Enter Second Number: "))
        result = float_addition(number1,number2) # Function Call
# Display Input and Output
        print("First Entered Number is ",number1)
        print("Second Entered Number is ",number2)
        print(f"Sum of {number1} and {number2} is {result} ")
    except ValueError:
        print("Error! Enter Integer/Float Value")

Program to check if it is an even number or odd number?

Return Type, No Arguments / Parameters

CODE
'''
Purpose of Program
The main purpose of this Python Program is to demonstrate how we can use Functions to calculate if a number is even or odd and
display it on the Output Screen. Please note that the Function Prototype will be: No Return Type, No Arguments / Parameters
This program comprises of two Functions.
1. main()
2. check_even_odd()
'''

# Function Prototypes for User Defined Functions
# void check_even_odd(); # Function Prototype
def check_even_odd():
    try:
# Input
# Variable to store Input - number
# Variable to store Output - N/A
        number = int(input("Enter a Number: "))
# Processing + Output
        if number % 2 == 0:
            num = 'even'
        elif number % 2 != 0:
            num = 'odd'
# RETRUN result (Output) to the Calling Function
        return num
    except ValueError:
        print("Error! Enter Integer/Float Value")
if __name__ == "__main__": # main() Function
# When a function returns a value, use Assignment Statement ot Call Function
    result = check_even_odd() # Function Call
    # Printing Output
    if result == 'even':
        print("It is an Even Number")
    elif result == 'odd':
        print("It is an Odd Number")
Enter a Number:  45

It is an Odd Number

Return Type, Arguments / Parameters

CODE
'''
Purpose of Program
The main purpose of this Python Program is to demonstrate how we can use Functions to calculate if a number is even or odd and
display it on the Output Screen. Please note that the Function Prototype will be: Return Type, Arguments / Parameters
This program comprises of two Functions.
1. main()
2. check_even_odd()
'''

# Function Prototypes for User Defined Functions
# string check_even_odd(number); # Function Prototype
def check_even_odd(number):
# Processing + Output
        if number % 2 == 0:
            num = 'even'
        elif number % 2 != 0:
            num = 'odd'
# RETRUN result (Output) to the Calling Function
        return num
    
if __name__ == "__main__": # main() Function
    try:
# Input
# Variable to store Input - number
# Variable to store Output - result
        number = int(input("Enter a Number: "))
# When a function returns a value, use Assignment Statement ot Call Function
        result = check_even_odd(number) # Function Call
# Printing Output
        if result == 'even':
            print("It is an Even Number")
        elif result == 'odd':
            print("It is an Odd Number")
    except ValueError:
        print("Error! Enter Integer/Float Value")
Enter a Number:  a

Error! Enter Integer/Float Value

TODO Task 1

• Consider the following Strings and answer the questions given below

String 1
    Hazrat Muhammad (PBUH) is the last Messenger of Allah.
String 2
    Hazrat Muhammad (PBUH) is the last Messenger of Allah. He’s (PBUH) role model for us in all fields of life.
String 3
    Hazrat Muhammad (PBUH) is the last Messenger of Allah.
    He’s (PBUH) role model for us in all fields of life.
    One who doesn’t accept Hazrat Muhammad (PBUH) as the last Messenger of Allah is a non-Muslim.

Questions

• Print String 1 using Single Quotes, String 2 using Double Quotes and String 3 using Triple Quotes

• Print lengths of String 1, String 2, and String 3 using len() Function

'''
Purpose of Program
The main purpose of the program is to create a string using single, double, and triple quotes and measure their lengths
'''

# Input + Processing + Output

try:
    
# Using Single Quotes
    print('---Message with Single Quotes---') 
    print('Hazrat Muhammad (PBUH) is the last Messenger of Allah.')

# Using Double Quotes
    print("")
    print('---Message with Double Quotes---')
    print("Hazrat Muhammad (PBUH) is the last Messenger of Allah. He’s (PBUH) role model for us in all fields of life.")

# Using Triple Quotes
    print("")
    print('---Message with Triple Quotes---') 
    print('''Hazrat Muhammad (PBUH) is the last Messenger of Allah.
        He’s (PBUH) role model for us in all fields of life.
        One who doesn’t accept Hazrat Muhammad (PBUH) as the last Messenger of Allah is a non-Muslim.''')
    print("")

# Calculating Length of String with Single Quotes using len() Function
    print('---Length of String with Single Quotes---')
    print('Length of "Hazrat Muhammad (PBUH) is the last Messenger of Allah." is: ', len("Hazrat Muhammad (PBUH) is the last Messenger of Allah."))
    print("")

# Calculating Length of String with Double Quotes using len() Function
    print('---Length of String with Double Quotes---')
    print("Hazrat Muhammad (PBUH) is the last Messenger of Allah. He’s (PBUH) role model for us in all fields of life.' is: ", len("Hazrat Muhammad (PBUH) is the last Messenger of Allah. He’s (PBUH) role model for us in all fields of life."))
    print("")
                                                                                   
# Calculating Length of String with Triple Quotes using len() Function
    print('---Length of String with Triple Quotes---') 
    print('''Length of 'Hazrat Muhammad (PBUH) is the last Messenger of Allah.
        He’s (PBUH) role model for us in all fields of life.
        One who doesn’t accept Hazrat Muhammad (PBUH) as the last Messenger of Allah is a non-Muslim.' is: ''', len("Hazrat Muhammad (PBUH) is the last Messenger of Allah. He’s (PBUH) role model for us in all fields of life. One who doesn’t accept Hazrat Muhammad (PBUH) as the last Messenger of Allah is a non-Muslim."))
                                                                                   
except:
    print('Error Occurred')

o Print String 1 using Single Quotes, String 2 using Double Quotes and String 3 using Triple Quotes
o Print lengths and types of String 1, String 2, and String 3 using len() Function
'''
Purpose of Program
The main purpose of the program is to create a string using single, double, and triple quotes and measure their lengths
'''

# Input + Processing + Output

try:
    
# Using Single Quotes
    print('---Message with Single Quotes---') 
    message_1 = 'Hazrat Muhammad (PBUH) is the last Messenger of Allah.'
    print("message_1 = "+ message_1) 
    print("Length of message_1 =", len(message_1)) 
    print("Data Type of message_1 =", type(message_1)) 
    print("")

# Using Double Quotes
    print('---Message with Double Quotes---')
    message_2 = "Hazrat Muhammad (PBUH) is the last Messenger of Allah. He’s (PBUH) role model for us in all fields of life."
    print("message_2 = "+ message_2) 
    print("Length of message_2 =", len(message_2)) 
    print("Data Type of message_2 =", type(message_2)) 
    print("")

# Using Triple Quotes
    print('---Message with Triple Quotes---') 
    message_3 = '''Hazrat Muhammad (PBUH) is the last Messenger of Allah.
        He’s (PBUH) role model for us in all fields of life.
        One who doesn’t accept Hazrat Muhammad (PBUH) as the last Messenger of Allah is a non-Muslim.'''
    print("message_3 = "+ message_3) 
    print("Length of message_3 =", len(message_3)) 
    print("Data Type of message_3 =", type(message_3)) 
    print("")

except:
    print('Error Occurred')
---Message with Single Quotes---
message_1 = Hazrat Muhammad (PBUH) is the last Messenger of Allah.
Length of message_1 = 54
Data Type of message_1 = <class 'str'>

---Message with Double Quotes---
message_2 = Hazrat Muhammad (PBUH) is the last Messenger of Allah. He’s (PBUH) role model for us in all fields of life.
Length of message_2 = 107
Data Type of message_2 = <class 'str'>

---Message with Triple Quotes---
message_3 = Hazrat Muhammad (PBUH) is the last Messenger of Allah.
        He’s (PBUH) role model for us in all fields of life.
        One who doesn’t accept Hazrat Muhammad (PBUH) as the last Messenger of Allah is a non-Muslim.
Length of message_3 = 217
Data Type of message_3 = <class 'str'>

TODO Task 3

● Consider the following String and answer the questions given below

String 1: Hazrat Muhammad (PBUH) is the last Messenger of Allah.

● Questions

o Apply following functions on String 1 and print the original and new string on the Output Screen?
    ▪ title()
    ▪ capitalize()
    ▪ upper()
    ▪ lower()
    ▪ center()
'''
Purpose of Program
The main purpose of the program is to format string using following built-in Functions i.e., 
title(), capitalize(), upper(), lower() and center()
'''

# Input + Processing + Output
try:

# Initialize a Message
    message = 'Hazrat Muhammad (PBUH) is the last Messenger of Allah.'

# Using title() Function
    print('---Original String before using title() Function---')
    print(message)
    print("")

    print('---New String after using title() Function---')
    print(message.title())

# Using capitalize() Function
    print("")
    print('---Original String before using capitalize() Function---') 
    print(message)
    print("")

    print('---New String after using capitalize() Function---') 
    print(message.capitalize())

# Using upper() Function
    print("")
    print('---Original String before using upper() Function---') 
    print(message)
    print("")

    print('---New String after using upper() Function---') 
    print(message.upper())

# Using lower() Function
    print("")
    print('---Original String before using lower() Function---') 
    print(message)
    print("")

    print('---New String after using lower() Function---') 
    print(message.lower())

# Using center() Function
    print("")
    print('---Original String before using center() Function---') 
    print("Original Message: "+ message)
    print("")

    print('---New String after using center() Function---') 
    print(message.center(100))

except:
    print('Error Occurred')

''' Purpose of Program
The main purpose of the program is to access elements from a string using indexing,
slicing and split() function '''

# Input + Processing + Output

try:
    
# Initialize a Message
    message = 'Hazrat Muhammad (PBUH) is role model for us in all fields of life.'

# Accessing Elements of a String using Indexing
    print("")
    print('---Original String before Indexing---') 
    print(message)
    print("")
    print('---New String after Indexing---')

# Access First Element of String
    print("Access Element at First Index i.e., message[0] is: "+ message[0])

# Access 14th Element of String
    print("Access Element at 14th Index i.e., message[14] is: "+ message[14])

# Access Last Element of String
    print("Access Element at last Index i.e., message[-1] is: "+ message[-1])

# Using Slicing
    print("")
    print('---Original String before Slicing---') 
    print(message)
    print("")
    print('---New String after Slicing---')

# Access First Sentence of String with stop value only i.e., [:13]
    print("Access First Sentence of String with stop value only i.e., [:13]: "+ message[:13])

# Access First Sentence of String with both start and stop value i.e., [0:13] 
    print("Access First Sentence of String with both start and stop value i.e.,[0:13]: "+ message[0:13])

# Access Middle Sentence of String
    print("Access Element from Middle Sentence i.e., message[14:53]: "+ message[14:53])

# Access Last Sentence of String with start value only i.e., message[55:]
    print("Access Last Sentence of String with start value only i.e., message[55:]: "+ message[55:])
    
# Access Last Sentence of String with both start and stop value i.e., [55:91] 
    print("Access Element from Last Sentence i.e.,message[55:91]: "+ message[55:91])

# Split String on basis of full stop (.) using split() Function
    print("")
    print('---Original String before using split() Function---') 
    print(message)
    print("")
    print('---New String after using split() Function---')
    print(message.split('.'))

# Split String on basis of spaces using split() Function 
    print("")
    print('---Original String before using split() Function---') 
    print(message)
    print("")
    print('---New String after using split() Function---') 
    print(message.split(' '))

except:
    print('Error Occurred')

Access Element at last Index i.e., message[-1] is: .

''' Purpose of Program
The main purpose of the program is to insert character at start of a string and display the result on the Output Screen '''

# Input + Processing + Output
try:
    
# Initialize Variable
    message = 'Hazrat Muhammad (PBUH) is role model for us in all fields of life.'
    print('---Original String before using + Operator---')
    print(message)
    print("")

# Using + Operator to insert Element at First Index of a String 
    new_message = "*" + message[0:]
    print('---New String after using + Operator ---') 
    print(new_message)
    print("")

# Using join() Function to insert Element at First Index of a String
    print('---Original String before using join() Function---') 
    print(message)
    print("")
    newmessage = ''.join(("*",message))
    print('---New String after using join() Function---') 
    print(newmessage)
    print("")
    
# Using % Operator to insert Element at First Index of a String
    print('---Original String before using % Operator---') 
    print(message)
    print("")
    new_message = "%sHazrat Muhammad (PBUH) is role model for us in all fields of life." %'*'
    print('---New String after using % Operator---')
    print(new_message)
    print("")
    
# Using format() Function to insert Element at First Index of a String
    print('---Original String before using format() Function---') 
    print(message)
    print("")
    new_message = "{}Hazrat Muhammad (PBUH) is role model for us in all fields of life.".format('*')
    print('---New String after using format() Function---')
    print(new_message)
    print("")
    
# Using f Prefix to insert Element at First Index of a String
    print('---Original String before using f Prefix---') 
    print(message)
    print("")
    new_message = f"{'*'}Hazrat Muhammad (PBUH) is role model for us in all fields of life."
    print('---New String after using f Prefix---') 
    print(new_message)
    print("")
    
# Using find() Function to insert Element at First Index of a String
    print('---Original String before using find() Function---') 
    print(message)
    print("")
    index = message.find('Hazrat')
    final_string = '*' + message[index:]
    print('---New String after using find() Function---') 
    print(final_string)
    print("")
# Using split(), join() and insert() Functions to insert Element at First Index of a String 
    print('---Original String before using split() Function---') 
    print(message)
    split_strings = message.split()
    split_strings.insert(0, '*') 
    updated_string = ' '.join(split_strings)
    print('---New String after using split() Function---') 
    print(updated_string)
except:
    print('Error Occurred')

● Consider the following String and answer the questions given below

String 1: Muhammad

● Questions

o Traverse String 1 using the methods presented in this Chapter?

Method 1

''' Purpose of Program 
The main purpose of the program is to traverse an entire string and display the result on the Output Screen '''

# Input + Processing + Output
try: 
# Initialize Variable 
    message = 'Muhammad' 
# Traverse an entire String
    print(message) 
except: 
    print('Error Occurred')

Method 2

'''
Purpose of Program
The main purpose of the program is to traverse a string (element by element) and display the result 
on the Output Screen
'''

# Input + Processing + Output
try:
    
# ---Approach I - Iterate over a string (element by element) using for loop---
# Initialize Variable 
    message_1 = 'Muhammad'
# Iterate over a string (element by element) using for loop
    print(" ---Approach I - Iterate over a string (element by element) using for loop---")
    print("---Traverse a String (Element by Element) using for Loop---")
    for character in message_1:
        print(character)
# ---Approach II - Iterate over a string (element by element) using Indexing---

# Initialize Variable 
    message_2 = 'Muhammad'

# Iterate over a string (element by element) using for loop with Indexing
    print(" ---Approach II - Iterate over a string (element by element) using Indexing---")
    print("---Traverse a String (Element by Element) using for Loop with Indexing---")
    for element in range(0, len(message_2)):
        print("message_2[",element,"]: " + message_2[element])
        
# ---Approach III - Iterate over a string (element by element) using Slicing---
# Initialize Variable
    message_3 = 'Muhammad' 
    counter = 0
    print("---Approach III - Iterate over a string (element by element) using Slicing---")

# Iterate over a string (element by element) using for loop with Slicing
    print("---Traverse a String (Element by Element) using for Loop with Slicing--- ")
    
# Slicing Operator => string[starting index : ending index : step value] 
    for element in message_3[0 : len(message_3): 1]:
        counter = counter + 1 
        print("message_3[",counter,"]: " + element)
except:
    print('Error Occurred')
 ---Approach I - Iterate over a string (element by element) using for loop---
---Traverse a String (Element by Element) using for Loop---
M
u
h
a
m
m
a
d
 ---Approach II - Iterate over a string (element by element) using Indexing---
---Traverse a String (Element by Element) using for Loop with Indexing---
message_2[ 0 ]: M
message_2[ 1 ]: u
message_2[ 2 ]: h
message_2[ 3 ]: a
message_2[ 4 ]: m
message_2[ 5 ]: m
message_2[ 6 ]: a
message_2[ 7 ]: d
---Approach III - Iterate over a string (element by element) using Slicing---
---Traverse a String (Element by Element) using for Loop with Slicing---

    ▪ z

'''

# Input + Processing + Output
try:

    message = 'Hazrat Muhammad (PBUH) is role model for us in all fields of life.'

    print(message) 
    print("")
    index_of_character = message.find('z') 
    print('Searching all instances of a Search Term (z)') 
    print(index_of_character) 
    print("") 

# Using split() and find() Function to Search a String using for Loop 
    split_message = message.split() 
    for elem in split_message: 
        index = elem.find("Muhammad") 
        if index != -1: 
            print(elem) 
except: 
    print('Error Occurred')
---Original String before using find() Function---
Hazrat Muhammad (PBUH) is role model for us in all fields of life.

---Index of Searched Term (PBUH) returned by Search Function---
17

---Original String before using find() Function---
Hazrat Muhammad (PBUH) is role model for us in all fields of life.

Searching all instances of a Search Term (z)
2

Muhammad

def displayUserInformation(cnic_no, address, country): 
    print("CNIC NO.: ", cnic_no)
    print("Address: ",address)
    print("Country: ",country)

# Input
        cnic_no = input("Enter your CNIC NO.:") 
        address = input("Enter your Address: ")
        country = input("Enter your Country:")
        print("")

    except ValueError:
        print("Error! Enter Valid Values")

Slicing

'''
Purpose of Program
The main purpose of the program is to access element(s) of a list using slicing and display the 
result on the output screen
'''
try:
# Initialize List 
    prophets = ['Hazrat Muhammad (PBUH)', 'Hazrat Ibrahim (A.S.)', 'Hazrat Mosa (A.S.)', 'Hazrat Isa (A.S.)', 'Hazrat Adam (A.S.)']
    ages = [25, 30, 15, 20, 22, 33]
    
# Access Element(s) of First List using Slicing
    print("---Access Element(s) of First List using Slicing---")
    print("")
    print("prophets[2:4]:",prophets[2:4])
    print("")

# Access from 2nd element till 4th element
    print("prophets[1:4]:", prophets[1:4])
    print("")

# Access from start till 3rd element 
    print("prophets[:3]:", prophets[:3])
    print("")

# Access from 2nd element till end
    print("prophets[1:]:", prophets[1:])
    print("")

# Access from start till 3rd last element 
    print("prophets[:-2]:", prophets[:-2]) 
    print("")

# Access from 3rd last element till 1st last element 
    print("prophets[-3:-1]:", prophets[-3:-1]) 
    print("")

# Access from 2nd element till 2nd last element
    print("prophets[1:-1]:", prophets[1:-1])
    print("")

# Access all elements 
    print("prophets[:]:",prophets[:]) 
    print("")
    
# Access Element(s) of Second List using Slicing
    print("---Access Element(s) of Second List using Slicing---")
    print("")
    print("ages[2:4]:",ages[2:4])
    print("")

# Access from 2nd element till 4th element
    print("ages[1:4]:", ages[1:4])
    print("")

# Access from start till 3rd element 
    print("ages[:3]:", ages[:3])
    print("")

# Access from 2nd element till end
    print("ages[1:]:", ages[1:])
    print("")

# Access from start till 3rd last element 
    print("ages[:-2]:", ages[:-2]) 
    print("")

# Access from 3rd last element till 1st last element 
    print("ages[-3:-1]:", ages[-3:-1]) 
    print("")

# Access from 2nd element till 2nd last element
    print("ages[1:-1]:", ages[1:-1])
    print("")

# Access all elements 
    print("ages[:]:",ages[:]) 
    print("")

except: 
    print("Error Occurred")
---Access Element(s) of First List using Slicing---

prophets[2:4]: ['Hazrat Mosa (A.S.)', 'Hazrat Isa (A.S.)']

prophets[1:4]: ['Hazrat Ibrahim (A.S.)', 'Hazrat Mosa (A.S.)', 'Hazrat Isa (A.S.)']

prophets[:3]: ['Hazrat Muhammad (PBUH)', 'Hazrat Ibrahim (A.S.)', 'Hazrat Mosa (A.S.)']

prophets[1:]: ['Hazrat Ibrahim (A.S.)', 'Hazrat Mosa (A.S.)', 'Hazrat Isa (A.S.)', 'Hazrat Adam (A.S.)']

prophets[:-2]: ['Hazrat Muhammad (PBUH)', 'Hazrat Ibrahim (A.S.)', 'Hazrat Mosa (A.S.)']

prophets[-3:-1]: ['Hazrat Mosa (A.S.)', 'Hazrat Isa (A.S.)']

prophets[1:-1]: ['Hazrat Ibrahim (A.S.)', 'Hazrat Mosa (A.S.)', 'Hazrat Isa (A.S.)']

prophets[:]: ['Hazrat Muhammad (PBUH)', 'Hazrat Ibrahim (A.S.)', 'Hazrat Mosa (A.S.)', 'Hazrat Isa (A.S.)', 'Hazrat Adam (A.S.)']

---Access Element(s) of Second List using Slicing---

Method 1

'''
Purpose of Program
The main purpose of the program is to add a new element at the start of a list '''

try:
    print("---Add a Single Element at Start of First List---")

# List Initialization
    prophets = ['Hazrat Muhammad (PBUH)', 'Hazrat Ibrahim (A.S.)', 'Hazrat Mosa (A.S.)', 'Hazrat Isa (A.S.)', 'Hazrat Adam (A.S.)']
    print("---Original List before Adding Element at Start of First List---") 
    print("")
    print(prophets)
    print("")

    prophets.insert(0,"Hazrat Yousaf (A.S.)")
    print("")
                                                                                                      
# Display Updated List after Adding Element at Start of First List
    print("---Updated List after Adding Element at Start of First List---") 
    print("")
    print(prophets)
    print("")
except:
    print("Error Occurred")

print("-------------------------------------------------------------")

    print("---Add a Single Element at Start of Second List---")

    print("")

    print("")

    print("---Updated List after Adding Element at Start of a List---")

    print(ages)
    print("")

    print("Error Occurred")

Purpose of Program

try:
# Iterate over First List (element by element) using for loop---

# List Initialization
    prophets = ['Hazrat Muhammad (PBUH)', 'Hazrat Ibrahim (A.S.)', 'Hazrat Mosa (A.S.)', 'Hazrat Isa (A.S.)', 'Hazrat Adam (A.S.)']
    ages = [25, 30, 15, 20, 22, 33]

# Iterate over First List (element by element) using for loop
    print("Iterate over First List (element by element) using for loop---")
    print("")
    print("---Traverse First List (Element by Element) using for Loop---")
    print("")
    for element in prophets:
        print (element)
    print("")
    
# Iterate over Second List (element by element) using for loop
    print("Iterate over Second List (element by element) using for loop---")
    print("")
    print("---Traverse Second List (Element by Element) using for Loop---")
    print("")
    for element in ages:
        print (element)
except:
    print('Error Occurred')

o Sort Elements of the selected lists using following methods (as shown in this Chapter)
    ▪   Method 1: Sort a List Alphabetically
    ▪   Method 2: Sort a List in Ascending Order
    ▪   Method 3: Sort a List in Descending Order

Method 1

'''
Purpose of Program
The main purpose of the program is to sort a list alphabetically '''
try:
# Initialize List
    prophets = ['Hazrat Muhammad (PBUH)', 'Hazrat Ibrahim (A.S.)', 'Hazrat Mosa (A.S.)', 'Hazrat Isa (A.S.)', 'Hazrat Adam (A.S.)']
    ages = [25, 30, 15, 20, 22, 33]
    
    print('---Original First List before using sort() Function---')
    print("")
    print(prophets)
    print("")
    
# Using sort() Function to sort First List Alphabetically 
    prophets.sort()
    print('---New First List after using sort() Function---') 
    print("")
    print(prophets)
    print("")
    
    print('---Original Second List before using sort() Function---')
    print("")
    print(ages)
    print("")
    
# Using sort() Function to sort Second List Alphabetically 
    ages.sort()
    print('---New Second List after using sort() Function---') 
    print("")
    print(ages)
    print("")    
except:
    print('Error Occurred')
---Original First List before using sort() Function---

['Hazrat Muhammad (PBUH)', 'Hazrat Ibrahim (A.S.)', 'Hazrat Mosa (A.S.)', 'Hazrat Isa (A.S.)', 'Hazrat Adam (A.S.)']

---New First List after using sort() Function---

['Hazrat Adam (A.S.)', 'Hazrat Ibrahim (A.S.)', 'Hazrat Isa (A.S.)', 'Hazrat Mosa (A.S.)', 'Hazrat Muhammad (PBUH)']

---Original Second List before using sort() Function---

[25, 30, 15, 20, 22, 33]

---New Second List after using sort() Function---

[15, 20, 22, 25, 30, 33]

'''
Purpose of Program
The main purpose of the program is to sort a list alphabetically '''
try:
# Initialize List
    prophets = ['Hazrat Muhammad (PBUH)', 'Hazrat Ibrahim (A.S.)', 'Hazrat Mosa (A.S.)', 'Hazrat Isa (A.S.)', 'Hazrat Adam (A.S.)']
    ages = [25, 30, 15, 20, 22, 33]
    
    print('---Original First List before using sort() Function---')
    print("")
    print(prophets)
    print("")
    
# Using sort() Function to sort First List Alphabetically 
    prophets.sort(reverse = False)
    print('---New First List after using sort() Function---')

    print("")

    print("")
    print(ages)
    print("")

    print("")

    print('Error Occurred')

● Questions

o Merge Elements of the selected lists using following methods (as shown in this Chapter)
    ▪   Method 1: Concatenate Lists using + Operator
    ▪   Method 2: Concatenate Lists using * Operator
    ▪   Method 3: Merge Lists using append() Function
    ▪   Method 4: Merge Lists using extend() Function

Method 1

'''
Purpose of Program
The main purpose of the program is to concatenate lists using + operator '''
try:
# Initialize List
    prophets = ['Hazrat Muhammad (PBUH)', 'Hazrat Ibrahim (A.S.)', 'Hazrat Mosa (A.S.)', 'Hazrat Isa (A.S.)', 'Hazrat Adam (A.S.)']
    ages = [25, 30, 15, 20, 22, 33]
    
    print('---Original Lists before Merging---')
    print("")
    print(prophets)
    print("")
    print(ages)
    print("")
    
# Using + Operator to Concatenate Lists 
    print('---New List after Merging---') 
    for count in range(len(prophets)):
        Merge_prophets_ages = prophets[count] + " - " + str(ages[count]) 
        print(Merge_prophets_ages)    

except:
    print('Error Occurred')

---Original Lists before Merging---

['Hazrat Muhammad (PBUH)', 'Hazrat Ibrahim (A.S.)', 'Hazrat Mosa (A.S.)', 'Hazrat Isa (A.S.)', 'Hazrat Adam (A.S.)']

[25, 30, 15, 20, 22, 33]

---New List after Merging---
Hazrat Muhammad (PBUH) - 25
Hazrat Ibrahim (A.S.) - 30
Hazrat Mosa (A.S.) - 15
Hazrat Isa (A.S.) - 20
Hazrat Adam (A.S.) - 22

Method 2

'''
Purpose of Program
The main purpose of the program is to concatenate lists using * operator '''
try:
# Initialize List
    prophets = ['Hazrat Muhammad (PBUH)', 'Hazrat Ibrahim (A.S.)', 'Hazrat Mosa (A.S.)', 'Hazrat Isa (A.S.)', 'Hazrat Adam (A.S.)']
    ages = [25, 30, 15, 20, 22, 33]
    
    print('---Original Lists before Merging---')
    print("")
    print(prophets)
    print("")
    print(ages)
    print("")
    
# Using * Operator to Concatenate Lists 
    print('---New List after Merging---') 
    for count in range(len(prophets)):
        Merge_prophets_ages = [*(prophets[count],ages[count] )] 
        print(Merge_prophets_ages)    

except:
    print('Error Occurred')

---Original Lists before Merging---

['Hazrat Muhammad (PBUH)', 'Hazrat Ibrahim (A.S.)', 'Hazrat Mosa (A.S.)', 'Hazrat Isa (A.S.)', 'Hazrat Adam (A.S.)']

[25, 30, 15, 20, 22, 33]

---New List after Merging---
['Hazrat Muhammad (PBUH)', 25]
['Hazrat Ibrahim (A.S.)', 30]
['Hazrat Mosa (A.S.)', 15]
['Hazrat Isa (A.S.)', 20]
['Hazrat Adam (A.S.)', 22]

Method 3

'''
Purpose of Program
The main purpose of the program is to concatenate lists using append () Function '''
try:
# Initialize List
    prophets = ['Hazrat Muhammad (PBUH)', 'Hazrat Ibrahim (A.S.)', 'Hazrat Mosa (A.S.)', 'Hazrat Isa (A.S.)', 'Hazrat Adam (A.S.)']
    ages = [25, 30, 15, 20, 22, 33]
    
    print('---Original Lists before Merging---')
    print("")
    print(prophets)
    print("")
    print(ages)
    print("")
    
# Using append () Function to Concatenate Lists 
    print('---New List after Merging---') 
    for element in ages:
        prophets.append(element) 
    print(prophets)    

except:
    print('Error Occurred')

---Original Lists before Merging---

['Hazrat Muhammad (PBUH)', 'Hazrat Ibrahim (A.S.)', 'Hazrat Mosa (A.S.)', 'Hazrat Isa (A.S.)', 'Hazrat Adam (A.S.)']

[25, 30, 15, 20, 22, 33]

---New List after Merging---
['Hazrat Muhammad (PBUH)', 'Hazrat Ibrahim (A.S.)', 'Hazrat Mosa (A.S.)', 'Hazrat Isa (A.S.)', 'Hazrat Adam (A.S.)', 25, 30, 15, 20, 22, 33]

Method 4

'''
Purpose of Program
The main purpose of the program is to concatenate lists using extend () Function '''
try:
# Initialize List
    prophets = ['Hazrat Muhammad (PBUH)', 'Hazrat Ibrahim (A.S.)', 'Hazrat Mosa (A.S.)', 'Hazrat Isa (A.S.)', 'Hazrat Adam (A.S.)']
    ages = [25, 30, 15, 20, 22, 33]
    
    print('---Original Lists before Merging---')
    print("")
    print(prophets)
    print("")
    print(ages)
    print("")
    
# Using extend () Function to Concatenate Lists 
    print('---New List after Merging---') 
    print("")
    prophets.extend(ages)
    print(prophets)    

except:
    print('Error Occurred')

---Original Lists before Merging---

['Hazrat Muhammad (PBUH)', 'Hazrat Ibrahim (A.S.)', 'Hazrat Mosa (A.S.)', 'Hazrat Isa (A.S.)', 'Hazrat Adam (A.S.)']

[25, 30, 15, 20, 22, 33]

---New List after Merging---

['Hazrat Muhammad (PBUH)', 'Hazrat Ibrahim (A.S.)', 'Hazrat Mosa (A.S.)', 'Hazrat Isa (A.S.)', 'Hazrat Adam (A.S.)', 25, 30, 15, 20, 22, 33]

    prophets = ['Hazrat Muhammad (PBUH)', 'Hazrat Ibrahim (A.S.)', 'Hazrat Mosa (A.S.)', 'Hazrat Isa (A.S.)', 'Hazrat Adam (A.S.)']

    print(prophets)

''' Purpose of Program

try: 
# List Initialization 
    list_of_cars = ['Mehran', 'Mercedes', 'Cultus', 'WagonR']
# Create a new list with element of previous List i.e., qul_shareef 
    list_comprehension = [element for element in list_of_cars if "M" in element]
    print("New List containing alphabet 'M':",list_comprehension)
    print("")
except:
    print("Error Occurred")

# List Initialization

    print("New List containing prime numbers less than 10:",list_comprehension)

    print("Error Occurred")

● Consider the following Lists and answer the questions given below

o list_of_cars = ['Mehran', 'Mercedes', 'Cultus', 'WagonR']
o prime_numbers = [2, 3, 5, 7, 11, 13, 17, 19]

● Questions

o Implement  the  concept  of  Lambda Function  using  the  following methods dicussed in this Chapter
    ▪   Method 1: Use filter() Function
    ▪   Method 2: Use map() Function

Method 1

''' Purpose of Program 
The main purpose of program is to filter only the cars with 'M' letter from the List and prime numbers less than 10'''

try: 
# List Initiazation 
    list_of_cars = ['Mehran', 'Mercedes', 'Cultus', 'WagonR']
    prime_numbers = [2, 3, 5, 7, 11, 13, 17, 19]
    print("---Origninal Lists before using filter() Function---")
    print("")
    print(list_of_cars)
    print("")
    print(prime_numbers)
    
# Lists after using filter() Function 
    print("")
    cars_with_m = list(filter(lambda car: 'M' in car, list_of_cars))
    print("---New Lists after using filter() Function---") 
    print('')
    print(cars_with_m)
    print('')
    
    updated_prime_numbers = list(filter(lambda number: number < 10, prime_numbers))
    print("---New List after using filter() Function---") 
    print('')
    print(updated_prime_numbers)
except: 
    print("Error Occurred")
---Origninal Lists before using filter() Function---

['Mehran', 'Mercedes', 'Cultus', 'WagonR']

[2, 3, 5, 7, 11, 13, 17, 19]

---New Lists after using filter() Function---

['Mehran', 'Mercedes']

---New List after using filter() Function---

[2, 3, 5, 7]

Method 2

''' Purpose of Program 
The main purpose of program is to add a specific number each item in a list using map() '''

try: 
# List Initiazation 
    list_of_cars = ['Mehran', 'Mercedes', 'Cultus', 'WagonR']
    prime_numbers = [2, 3, 5, 7, 11, 13, 17, 19]
    print("---Origninal Lists before using map() Function---")
    print("")
    print(list_of_cars)
    print("")
    print(prime_numbers)
    
# Lists after using filter() Function 
    print("")
    cars_with_m = list(map(lambda car: car.upper(), list_of_cars))
    print("---New Lists after using map() Function---") 
    print('')
    print(cars_with_m)
    print('')
    
    updated_prime_numbers = list(map(lambda number: number + 10, prime_numbers))
    print("---New List after using map() Function---") 
    print('')
    print(updated_prime_numbers)
except: 
    print("Error Occurred")
---Origninal Lists before using map() Function---

['Mehran', 'Mercedes', 'Cultus', 'WagonR']

[2, 3, 5, 7, 11, 13, 17, 19]

---New Lists after using map() Function---

['MEHRAN', 'MERCEDES', 'CULTUS', 'WAGONR']

---New List after using map() Function---

[12, 13, 15, 17, 21, 23, 27, 29]

The main purpose of the program is to initialize a complete dictionary and display its content (data values) on the Output Screen '''
try:
# Dictionary Initialization - Method 1: Use {} 
    print("---Dictionary Initialization - Use {}---")
    print ("")
    phone_directory = {'0348-6642185': 'Adeeb', 
                        '0321-4971961':'Saaliha',
                        '0321-5865463': 'Kamaal', 
                        '0321-4582322': 'Naaila', 
                        '0345-8071517': 'Zuhra', 
                        '0323-7654151':'Wajeeha'}
    
# Display Data Values of a Dictionary

    print ("")

    print ("")
    print("Data-Type of phone_directory:", type(phone_directory)) 


# Dictionary Initialization - Method 2: Use dict() Function 
    print ("")
    print("---Dictionary Initialization – Use dict() Function---")
    print ("")
    courses = dict({ 'Python':['Samavi','Narmeen','Awais','Rehan','Hassan','Hassan'], 
                'Human Engineering': ['Samavi','Narmeen','Awais','Rehan','Hassan','Hassan'], 
                'Spiritual Training Courses': ['Rehan','Awais','Ali','Ahmed','Sara','Zara','Mahnoor','Maira']})
    
# Display Data Values of a Dictionary
    print ("")
    print("Data Values of courses:", courses)

''' Purpose of Program

try:
# Dictionary Initialization 
    print ("")

                        '0321-4971961':'Saaliha',

                        '0323-7654151':'Wajeeha'}

    print("---Access Element(s) of a Dictionary using get() Function---") 
    print(phone_directory.get('0348-6642185')) 
    print(phone_directory.get('0321-4971961')) 
    print(phone_directory.get('0321-5865463')) 
    print(phone_directory.get('0321-4582322')) 
    print(phone_directory.get('0345-8071517')) 
    print(phone_directory.get('0323-7654151'))

    print(courses.get('Human Engineering')) 
    print(courses.get('Spiritual Training Courses')) 

except:

''' Purpose of Program

try:
# Dictionary Initialization 
    print ("")
    phone_directory = {'0348-6642185': 'Adeeb', 
                        '0321-4971961':'Saaliha',
                        '0321-5865463': 'Kamaal', 
                        '0321-4582322': 'Naaila', 
                        '0345-8071517': 'Zuhra', 
                        '0323-7654151':'Wajeeha'}
    
    print("---Original Dictionary before Adding Element at Start of a Dictionary---") 
    print("")
    print(phone_directory)
    
# Data Type of i.e., phone_directory before converting to List
    print("")
    print("---Data Type of i.e., phone_directory before converting to List---") 
    print("")
    print(type(phone_directory)) 
    
# Converting a Dictionary into a List and store list in "list_phone_directory" 
    print("")
    list_phone_directory = list(phone_directory.items()) 
    
# Data Type of i.e., phone_directory after converting to List 
    print("")
    print("---Data Type of i.e., phone_directory after converting to List---") 
    print("")
    print(type(list_phone_directory))
    
# Add Data Value at Start of a Dictionary using insert() Function 
    print("")
    list_phone_directory.insert(0, ('0321-1234567','Ahmed')) 

# Display Updated Dictionary after Adding Element at Start of a Dictionary 
    print("")
    print("---Updated Dictionary after Adding Element at Start of a Dictionary---") 
    print("")
    print(list_phone_directory) 

    
# Dictionary Initialization
    print ("")
    courses = { 'Python':['Samavi','Narmeen','Awais','Rehan','Hassan','Hassan'], 
                'Human Engineering': ['Samavi','Narmeen','Awais','Rehan','Hassan','Hassan'], 
                'Spiritual Training Courses': ['Rehan','Awais','Ali','Ahmed','Sara','Zara','Mahnoor','Maira']}
    
    print("---Original Dictionary before Adding Element at Start of a Dictionary---") 
    print("")
    print(courses)
    
# Data Type of i.e., courses before converting to List
    print("")
    print("---Data Type of i.e., courses before converting to List---") 
    print("")
    print(type(courses))

    print("")
    print("---Data Type of i.e., courses after converting to List---") 
    print("")

● Questions

o Traverse selected Dictionaries using following methods (as shown in this Chapter)
    ▪   Method 1: Traversing an Entire Dictionary
    ▪   Method 2: Traversing a Dictionary (Element by Element)

Method 1

''' Purpose of Program 
The main purpose of the program is to traverse through an entire dictionary and display the result on the output screen '''
try:
# Dictionary Initialization 
    print ("")
    phone_directory = {'0348-6642185': 'Adeeb', 
                        '0321-4971961':'Saaliha',
                        '0321-5865463': 'Kamaal', 
                        '0321-4582322': 'Naaila', 
                        '0345-8071517': 'Zuhra', 
                        '0323-7654151':'Wajeeha'}
    
# Traverse through all key, value pairs 
    print("---Traverse through all key, value pairs---") 
    print ("")
    for elements in phone_directory.items(): 
        print(elements)
        
# Dictionary Initialization 
    print ("")
    courses = { 'Python':['Samavi','Narmeen','Awais','Rehan','Hassan','Hassan'], 
                'Human Engineering': ['Samavi','Narmeen','Awais','Rehan','Hassan','Hassan'], 
                'Spiritual Training Courses': ['Rehan','Awais','Ali','Ahmed','Sara','Zara','Mahnoor','Maira']}
    
# Traverse through all key, value pairs 
    print("---Traverse through all key, value pairs---") 
    print ("")
    for elements in courses.items(): 
        print(elements)        
except: 
    print("Error Occurred")

---Traverse through all key, value pairs---

('0348-6642185', 'Adeeb')
('0321-4971961', 'Saaliha')
('0321-5865463', 'Kamaal')
('0321-4582322', 'Naaila')
('0345-8071517', 'Zuhra')
('0323-7654151', 'Wajeeha')

---Traverse through all key, value pairs---

('Python', ['Samavi', 'Narmeen', 'Awais', 'Rehan', 'Hassan', 'Hassan'])
('Human Engineering', ['Samavi', 'Narmeen', 'Awais', 'Rehan', 'Hassan', 'Hassan'])
('Spiritual Training Courses', ['Rehan', 'Awais', 'Ali', 'Ahmed', 'Sara', 'Zara', 'Mahnoor', 'Maira'])

Method 2

''' Purpose of Program 
The main purpose of the program is to traverse through a dictionary and display the result on the output screen '''
try:
# Dictionary Initialization 
    print ("")
    phone_directory = {'0348-6642185': 'Adeeb', 
                        '0321-4971961':'Saaliha',
                        '0321-5865463': 'Kamaal', 
                        '0321-4582322': 'Naaila', 
                        '0345-8071517': 'Zuhra', 
                        '0323-7654151':'Wajeeha'}
    
# Traverse through all key, value pairs 
    print("---Traverse through all keys of First Dictionary---") 
    print ("")
    for elements in phone_directory.keys(): 
        print(elements)
    print ("")
    print("---Traverse through all values of First Dictionary---") 
    print ("")
    for elements in phone_directory.values(): 
        print(elements)    
# Dictionary Initialization 
    print ("")
    courses = { 'Python':['Samavi','Narmeen','Awais','Rehan','Hassan','Hassan'], 
                'Human Engineering': ['Samavi','Narmeen','Awais','Rehan','Hassan','Hassan'], 
                'Spiritual Training Courses': ['Rehan','Awais','Ali','Ahmed','Sara','Zara','Mahnoor','Maira']}
    
# Traverse through all key, value pairs 
    print("---Traverse through all keys of Second Dictionary---") 
    print ("")
    for elements in courses.keys(): 
        print(elements)
    print ("") 
    print("---Traverse through all values of Second Dictionary---") 
    print ("")
    for elements in courses.values(): 
        print(elements) 
except: 
    print("Error Occurred")

0323-7654151

---Traverse through all values of First Dictionary---

---Traverse through all keys of Second Dictionary---

---Traverse through all values of Second Dictionary---

● Questions

o Search from selected Dictionaries using following methods (as shown in this Chapter)
    ▪   Method 1: Search Element(s) from a Dictionary using key
    ▪   Method 2: Search Element(s) from a Dictionary using value

Method 1

''' Purpose of Program 
The main purpose of the program is to search element(s) using key '''
try:
# Dictionary Initialization 
    print ("")
    phone_directory = {'0348-6642185': 'Adeeb', 
                        '0321-4971961':'Saaliha',
                        '0321-5865463': 'Kamaal', 
                        '0321-4582322': 'Naaila', 
                        '0345-8071517': 'Zuhra', 
                        '0323-7654151':'Wajeeha'}
    
# Search Value using Key from a Dictionary 
    print ("Value against '0348-6642185' : "+ phone_directory.get('0348-6642185'))
        
# Dictionary Initialization 
    print ("")
    courses =  {'Python':['Samavi','Narmeen','Awais','Rehan','Hassan','Hassan'], 
                'Human Engineering': ['Samavi','Narmeen','Awais','Rehan','Hassan','Hassan'], 
                'Spiritual Training Courses': ['Rehan','Awais','Ali','Ahmed','Sara','Zara','Mahnoor','Maira']}
    
# Search Value using Key from a Dictionary 
    print ("Value against 'Python' : " , courses.get('Python'))
except: 
    print("Error Occurred")

Value against '0348-6642185' : Adeeb

Value against 'Python' :  ['Samavi', 'Narmeen', 'Awais', 'Rehan', 'Hassan', 'Hassan']

Method 2

''' Purpose of Program 
The main purpose of the program is to search element(s) using value '''

try:
# Dictionary Initialization 
    print ("")
    phone_directory = {'0348-6642185': 'Adeeb', 
                        '0321-4971961':'Saaliha',
                        '0321-5865463': 'Kamaal', 
                        '0321-4582322': 'Naaila', 
                        '0345-8071517': 'Zuhra', 
                        '0323-7654151':'Wajeeha'}
    

    print("---Using Keys(), Values() and index()---")
    print("")

# Store all Keys from the Dictionary in the Variable i.e., key_list 
    key_list = list(phone_directory.keys())
    print("Keys in the Dictionary:", key_list)
    print("")

# Store all Values from the Dictionary in the Variable i.e., val_list 
    val_list = list(phone_directory.values())
    print("Values in the Dictionary:", val_list)
    print("")

    print("---------------------------------------------------------")
    print("")
# Store Index of Value 'Kamaal' in a Variable i.e., position 
    position_Kamaal = val_list.index('Kamaal')
# Display the Key with Value 'Kamaal'
    print("Key against Value 'Kamaal':",key_list[position_Kamaal])
    print("")

# Dictionary Initialization 
    print ("")
    courses =  {'Python':['Samavi','Narmeen','Awais','Rehan','Hassan','Hassan'], 
                'Human Engineering': ['Samavi','Narmeen','Awais','Rehan','Hassan','Hassan'], 
                'Spiritual Training Courses': ['Rehan','Awais','Ali','Ahmed','Sara','Zara','Mahnoor','Maira']}
    
    print("---Using Keys(), Values() and index()---")
    print("")

# Store all Keys from the Dictionary in the Variable i.e., key_list 
    key_list = list(courses.keys())
    print("Keys in the Dictionary:", key_list)
    print("")

# Store all Values from the Dictionary in the Variable i.e., val_list 
    val_list = list(courses.values())
    print("Values in the Dictionary:", val_list)
    print("")

    print("---------------------------------------------------------")
    print("")
# Store Index of Value ['Samavi','Narmeen','Awais','Rehan','Hassan','Hassan'] in a Variable i.e., position 
    position = val_list.index(['Samavi','Narmeen','Awais','Rehan','Hassan','Hassan'])
# Display the Key with Value ['Samavi','Narmeen','Awais','Rehan','Hassan','Hassan']
    print("Key against Value ['Samavi','Narmeen','Awais','Rehan','Hassan','Hassan']:",key_list[position])
    print("")
except: 
    print("Error Occurred")

---Using Keys(), Values() and index()---

Keys in the Dictionary: ['0348-6642185', '0321-4971961', '0321-5865463', '0321-4582322', '0345-8071517', '0323-7654151']

Values in the Dictionary: ['Adeeb', 'Saaliha', 'Kamaal', 'Naaila', 'Zuhra', 'Wajeeha']

---------------------------------------------------------

Key against Value 'Kamaal': 0321-5865463


---Using Keys(), Values() and index()---

Keys in the Dictionary: ['Python', 'Human Engineering', 'Spiritual Training Courses']

Values in the Dictionary: [['Samavi', 'Narmeen', 'Awais', 'Rehan', 'Hassan', 'Hassan'], ['Samavi', 'Narmeen', 'Awais', 'Rehan', 'Hassan', 'Hassan'], ['Rehan', 'Awais', 'Ali', 'Ahmed', 'Sara', 'Zara', 'Mahnoor', 'Maira']]

---------------------------------------------------------

Key against Value ['Samavi','Narmeen','Awais','Rehan','Hassan','Hassan']: Python

● Questions

o Sort the selected Dictionaries using following methods (as shown in this Chapter)
    ▪   Method 1: Sorting a Dictionary by key-value pair
    ▪   Method 2: Sorting a Dictionary by key
        ●  Method 2.1: Sorting a Dictionary by key in Ascending Order
        ●  Method 2.2: Sorting a Dictionary by key in Descending Order
    ▪   Method 3: Sorting a Dictionary by value
        ●  Method 3.1: Sorting a Dictionary by value in Ascending Order
        ●  Method 3.2: Sorting a Dictionary by value in Descending Order

Method 1

''' Purpose of Program 
The main purpose of the program is to sort a dictionary by key-value pair '''
try:
# Dictionary Initialization 
    print ("")
    phone_directory = {'0348-6642185': 'Adeeb', 
                        '0321-4971961':'Saaliha',
                        '0321-5865463': 'Kamaal', 
                        '0321-4582322': 'Naaila', 
                        '0345-8071517': 'Zuhra', 
                        '0323-7654151':'Wajeeha'}
    
    print("---Original Dictionary before Sorting---")
    print ("")
    print(phone_directory)
    print ("")
    
#Store key-value pair of a Dictionary using items() in Variable "dict_phone_directory" 
    dict_phone_directory = phone_directory.items()
    
# Sort Dictionary based on keys using sorted() Function
    sorted_dictionary_1 = sorted(dict_phone_directory) 
    print("---New Dictionary after Sorting---") 
    print ("")
    print(sorted_dictionary_1)

        
# Dictionary Initialization 
    print ("")
    courses =  {'Python':['Samavi','Narmeen','Awais','Rehan','Hassan','Hassan'], 
                'Human Engineering': ['Samavi','Narmeen','Awais','Rehan','Hassan','Hassan'], 
                'Spiritual Training Courses': ['Rehan','Awais','Ali','Ahmed','Sara','Zara','Mahnoor','Maira']}
    
    print("---Original Dictionary before Sorting---")
    print ("")
    print(courses)
    print ("")
    
#Store key-value pair of a Dictionary using items() in Variable "dict_courses" 
    dict_courses = courses.items()
    
# Sort Dictionary based on keys using sorted() Function
    sorted_dictionary_2 = sorted(dict_courses) 
    print("---New Dictionary after Sorting---") 
    print ("")
    print(sorted_dictionary_2)

except: 
    print("Error Occurred")

---Original Dictionary before Sorting---

{'0348-6642185': 'Adeeb', '0321-4971961': 'Saaliha', '0321-5865463': 'Kamaal', '0321-4582322': 'Naaila', '0345-8071517': 'Zuhra', '0323-7654151': 'Wajeeha'}

---New Dictionary after Sorting---

[('0321-4582322', 'Naaila'), ('0321-4971961', 'Saaliha'), ('0321-5865463', 'Kamaal'), ('0323-7654151', 'Wajeeha'), ('0345-8071517', 'Zuhra'), ('0348-6642185', 'Adeeb')]

---Original Dictionary before Sorting---

{'Python': ['Samavi', 'Narmeen', 'Awais', 'Rehan', 'Hassan', 'Hassan'], 'Human Engineering': ['Samavi', 'Narmeen', 'Awais', 'Rehan', 'Hassan', 'Hassan'], 'Spiritual Training Courses': ['Rehan', 'Awais', 'Ali', 'Ahmed', 'Sara', 'Zara', 'Mahnoor', 'Maira']}

---New Dictionary after Sorting---

[('Human Engineering', ['Samavi', 'Narmeen', 'Awais', 'Rehan', 'Hassan', 'Hassan']), ('Python', ['Samavi', 'Narmeen', 'Awais', 'Rehan', 'Hassan', 'Hassan']), ('Spiritual Training Courses', ['Rehan', 'Awais', 'Ali', 'Ahmed', 'Sara', 'Zara', 'Mahnoor', 'Maira'])]

Method 2.1

''' Purpose of Program 
The main purpose of the program is to sorting a dictionary by key in ascending order '''
try:
# Dictionary Initialization 
    print ("")
    phone_directory = {'0348-6642185': 'Adeeb', 
                        '0321-4971961':'Saaliha',
                        '0321-5865463': 'Kamaal', 
                        '0321-4582322': 'Naaila', 
                        '0345-8071517': 'Zuhra', 
                        '0323-7654151':'Wajeeha'}
    
    print("---Original Dictionary before Sorting---")
    print ("")
    print(phone_directory)
    print ("")
    
#Store key-value pair of a Dictionary using items() in Variable "dict_phone_directory" 
    dict_phone_directory = phone_directory.items()
    
# Sort Dictionary in ascending order using sorted() Function
    sorted_dictionary_1 = sorted(dict_phone_directory,reverse = False) 
    print("---New Dictionary after Sorting---") 
    print ("")
    print(sorted_dictionary_1)

        
# Dictionary Initialization 
    print ("")
    courses =  {'Python':['Samavi','Narmeen','Awais','Rehan','Hassan','Hassan'], 
                'Human Engineering': ['Samavi','Narmeen','Awais','Rehan','Hassan','Hassan'], 
                'Spiritual Training Courses': ['Rehan','Awais','Ali','Ahmed','Sara','Zara','Mahnoor','Maira']}
    
    print("---Original Dictionary before Sorting---")
    print ("")
    print(courses)
    print ("")
    
#Store key-value pair of a Dictionary using items() in Variable "dict_courses" 
    dict_courses = courses.items()
    
# Sort Dictionary in ascending order using sorted() Function
    sorted_dictionary_2 = sorted(dict_courses,reverse = False) 
    print("---New Dictionary after Sorting---") 
    print ("")
    print(sorted_dictionary_2)

except: 
    print("Error Occurred")

---Original Dictionary before Sorting---

---New Dictionary after Sorting---

[('0321-4582322', 'Naaila'), ('0321-4971961', 'Saaliha'), ('0321-5865463', 'Kamaal'), ('0323-7654151', 'Wajeeha'), ('0345-8071517', 'Zuhra'), ('0348-6642185', 'Adeeb')]

    print ("")

    sorted_dictionary_1 = sorted(dict_phone_directory,reverse = True)

# Dictionary Initialization

Method 3.1

''' Purpose of Program 
The main purpose of the program is to sorting a dictionary by value in descending order '''
try:
# Dictionary Initialization 
    print ("")
    phone_directory = {'0348-6642185': 'Adeeb', 
                        '0321-4971961':'Saaliha',
                        '0321-5865463': 'Kamaal', 
                        '0321-4582322': 'Naaila', 
                        '0345-8071517': 'Zuhra', 
                        '0323-7654151':'Wajeeha'}
    
# Sort Dictionary using 'get'
    print("---Sort Dictionary using 'get'---") 
    print ("")
    print("---Original Dictionary before Sorting---")
    print ("")
    print(phone_directory)
    print ("")
    print("---New Dictionary after Sorting---")
    print ("")
    for elements in sorted(phone_directory, key = phone_directory.get, reverse = False):
        print(elements, phone_directory[elements])
     
# Dictionary Initialization 
    print ("")
    courses =  {'Python':['Samavi','Narmeen','Awais','Rehan','Hassan','Hassan'], 
                'Human Engineering': ['Samavi','Narmeen','Awais','Rehan','Hassan','Hassan'], 
                'Spiritual Training Courses': ['Rehan','Awais','Ali','Ahmed','Sara','Zara','Mahnoor','Maira']}
    
# Sort Dictionary using 'get'
    print("---Sort Dictionary using 'get'---") 
    print ("")
    print("---Original Dictionary before Sorting---")
    print ("")
    print(courses)
    print ("")
    print("---New Dictionary after Sorting---")
    print ("")
    for elements in sorted(courses, key = courses.get, reverse = False):
        print(elements, courses[elements])

except: 
    print("Error Occurred")

● Questions

o Merge the selected Dictionaries using following methods (as shown in this Chapter)
    ▪   Method 1: Concatenate Dictionaries using update() Function
    ▪   Method 2: Concatenate Dictionaries using ** Operators

Method 1

''' Purpose of Program 
The main purpose of the program is to concatenate dictionaries using update() function '''
try:
# Dictionary Initialization 
    print ("")
    phone_directory = {'0348-6642185': 'Adeeb', 
                        '0321-4971961':'Saaliha',
                        '0321-5865463': 'Kamaal', 
                        '0321-4582322': 'Naaila', 
                        '0345-8071517': 'Zuhra', 
                        '0323-7654151':'Wajeeha'}
    courses = {'Python': ['Samavi','Narmeen','Awais','Rehan','Hassan','Hassan'],
                 'Human Engineering': ['Samavi','Narmeen','Awais','Rehan','Hassan','Hassan'],
                 'Spiritual Training Courses': ['Rehan','Awais','Ali','Ahmed','Sara','Zara','Mahnoor', 'Maira']}
    
    print("---Original Dictionary before Merge---")
    print ("\nDictionary 1\n")
    print(phone_directory)
    print ("\nDictionary 2\n")
    print(courses)
    print ("")

# Use update() Function to merge two Dictionaries
    phone_directory.update(courses) 
    print("---New Dictionary after Merge---") 
    print ("")
    print(phone_directory)

except: 
    print("Error Occurred")

---Original Dictionary before Merge---

Dictionary 1

{'0348-6642185': 'Adeeb', '0321-4971961': 'Saaliha', '0321-5865463': 'Kamaal', '0321-4582322': 'Naaila', '0345-8071517': 'Zuhra', '0323-7654151': 'Wajeeha'}

Dictionary 2

{'Python': ['Samavi', 'Narmeen', 'Awais', 'Rehan', 'Hassan', 'Hassan'], 'Human Engineering': ['Samavi', 'Narmeen', 'Awais', 'Rehan', 'Hassan', 'Hassan'], 'Spiritual Training Courses': ['Rehan', 'Awais', 'Ali', 'Ahmed', 'Sara', 'Zara', 'Mahnoor', 'Maira']}

---New Dictionary after Merge---

{'0348-6642185': 'Adeeb', '0321-4971961': 'Saaliha', '0321-5865463': 'Kamaal', '0321-4582322': 'Naaila', '0345-8071517': 'Zuhra', '0323-7654151': 'Wajeeha', 'Python': ['Samavi', 'Narmeen', 'Awais', 'Rehan', 'Hassan', 'Hassan'], 'Human Engineering': ['Samavi', 'Narmeen', 'Awais', 'Rehan', 'Hassan', 'Hassan'], 'Spiritual Training Courses': ['Rehan', 'Awais', 'Ali', 'Ahmed', 'Sara', 'Zara', 'Mahnoor', 'Maira']}

Method 2

''' Purpose of Program 
The main purpose of the program is to concatenate dictionaries using ** operator '''
try:
# Dictionary Initialization 
    print ("")
    phone_directory = {'0348-6642185': 'Adeeb', 
                        '0321-4971961':'Saaliha',
                        '0321-5865463': 'Kamaal', 
                        '0321-4582322': 'Naaila', 
                        '0345-8071517': 'Zuhra', 
                        '0323-7654151':'Wajeeha'}
    courses = {'Python': ['Samavi','Narmeen','Awais','Rehan','Hassan','Hassan'],
                 'Human Engineering': ['Samavi','Narmeen','Awais','Rehan','Hassan','Hassan'],
                 'Spiritual Training Courses': ['Rehan','Awais','Ali','Ahmed','Sara','Zara','Mahnoor', 'Maira']}
    
    print("---Original Dictionary before Merge---")
    print ("\nDictionary 1\n")
    print(phone_directory)
    print ("\nDictionary 2\n")
    print(courses)
    print ("")

# Use ** operator to merge two Dictionaries
    dict3_phone_directory = dict(phone_directory,** courses) 
    print("---New Dictionary after Merge---") 
    print ("")
    print(dict3_phone_directory)

except: 
    print("Error Occurred")

---Original Dictionary before Merge---

Dictionary 1

Dictionary 2

---New Dictionary after Merge---

{'0348-6642185': 'Adeeb', '0321-4971961': 'Saaliha', '0321-5865463': 'Kamaal', '0321-4582322': 'Naaila', '0345-8071517': 'Zuhra', '0323-7654151': 'Wajeeha', 'Python': ['Samavi', 'Narmeen', 'Awais', 'Rehan', 'Hassan', 'Hassan'], 'Human Engineering': ['Samavi', 'Narmeen', 'Awais', 'Rehan', 'Hassan', 'Hassan'], 'Spiritual Training Courses': ['Rehan', 'Awais', 'Ali', 'Ahmed', 'Sara', 'Zara', 'Mahnoor', 'Maira']}

● Questions

o Update the selected Dictionaries using following methods (as shown in this Chapter)
    ▪   Method 1: Update the key of a Dictionary using pop() Function
    ▪   Method 2: Update the value of a Dictionary
    ▪   Method 3: Update the value of a Dictionary using update() Function

Method 1

''' Purpose of Program 
The main purpose of the program is to update the key of a dictionary using pop() function '''
try:
# Dictionary Initialization 
    print ("")
    phone_directory = {'0348-6642185': 'Adeeb', 
                        '0321-4971961':'Saaliha',
                        '0321-5865463': 'Kamaal', 
                        '0321-4582322': 'Naaila', 
                        '0345-8071517': 'Zuhra', 
                        '0323-7654151':'Wajeeha'}
    
    print("---Original Dictionary before Updatation---")
    print ("")
    print(phone_directory)
    print ("")
    
# Use pop() Function to update old_key_value with new_key_value 
    new_key = "0321-1234567" 
    old_key = "0321-5865463" 
    phone_directory[new_key] = phone_directory.pop(old_key)
    print("---New Dictionary after Updatation---") 
    print(phone_directory)

    courses = {'Python': ['Samavi','Narmeen','Awais','Rehan','Hassan','Hassan'],
                 'Human Engineering': ['Samavi','Narmeen','Awais','Rehan','Hassan','Hassan'],
                 'Spiritual Training Courses': ['Rehan','Awais','Ali','Ahmed','Sara','Zara','Mahnoor', 'Maira']}
    print("---Original Dictionary before Updatation---")
    print ("")
    print(courses)
    print ("")
    
# Use pop() Function to update old_key_value with new_key_value 
    new_key = "Data Science" 
    old_key = "Spiritual Training Courses" 
    courses[new_key] = courses.pop(old_key)
    print("---New Dictionary after Updatation---") 
    print(courses)

except: 
    print("Error Occurred")

---Original Dictionary before Updatation---

{'0348-6642185': 'Adeeb', '0321-4971961': 'Saaliha', '0321-5865463': 'Kamaal', '0321-4582322': 'Naaila', '0345-8071517': 'Zuhra', '0323-7654151': 'Wajeeha'}

---New Dictionary after Updatation---
{'0348-6642185': 'Adeeb', '0321-4971961': 'Saaliha', '0321-4582322': 'Naaila', '0345-8071517': 'Zuhra', '0323-7654151': 'Wajeeha', '0321-1234567': 'Kamaal'}
---Original Dictionary before Updatation---

{'Python': ['Samavi', 'Narmeen', 'Awais', 'Rehan', 'Hassan', 'Hassan'], 'Human Engineering': ['Samavi', 'Narmeen', 'Awais', 'Rehan', 'Hassan', 'Hassan'], 'Spiritual Training Courses': ['Rehan', 'Awais', 'Ali', 'Ahmed', 'Sara', 'Zara', 'Mahnoor', 'Maira']}

---New Dictionary after Updatation---
{'Python': ['Samavi', 'Narmeen', 'Awais', 'Rehan', 'Hassan', 'Hassan'], 'Human Engineering': ['Samavi', 'Narmeen', 'Awais', 'Rehan', 'Hassan', 'Hassan'], 'Data Science': ['Rehan', 'Awais', 'Ali', 'Ahmed', 'Sara', 'Zara', 'Mahnoor', 'Maira']}

● Questions

o Remove  from  selected  Dictionaries  using  following  methods  (as shown in this Chapter)
    ▪   Method 1: Delete Entire / Element(s) from a Dictionary using del
    ▪   Method 2: Remove Element(s) of a Dictionary using clear() Function    
    ▪   Method 3: Remove Specific Element(s) from a Dictionary using pop() Function
    ▪   Method 4: Remove Last Element(s) from a Dictionary using popitem() Function

Method 1

''' Purpose of Program 
The main purpose of the program is to Delete Entire / Element(s) from a Dictionary using del '''
try:
# Dictionary Initialization 
    print ("")
    phone_directory = {'0348-6642185': 'Adeeb', 
                        '0321-4971961':'Saaliha',
                        '0321-5865463': 'Kamaal', 
                        '0321-4582322': 'Naaila', 
                        '0345-8071517': 'Zuhra', 
                        '0323-7654151':'Wajeeha'}
    
# Approach I - Delete Specific Element from Dictionary 
    print("---Approach I - Delete Specific Element from Dictionary---") 
    print ("")
    print("---Original Dictionary before Deleting---")
    print ("")
    print(phone_directory) 

# Use del to delete specific key-value pair from a Dictionary 
    del phone_directory['0345-8071517'] 
    print ("")
    print("---New Dictionary after Deleting---") 
    print ("")
    print(phone_directory)

    courses = {'Python': ['Samavi','Narmeen','Awais','Rehan','Hassan','Hassan'],
                 'Human Engineering': ['Samavi','Narmeen','Awais','Rehan','Hassan','Hassan'],
                 'Spiritual Training Courses': ['Rehan','Awais','Ali','Ahmed','Sara','Zara','Mahnoor', 'Maira']}

# Approach II - Delete Entire Dictionary 
    print ("")
    print("---Approach II - Delete Entire Dictionary---") 
    print ("")
    print("---Original Dictionary before Deleting---")
    print ("")
    print(courses) 

# Use del to delete specific key-value pair from a Dictionary
    del courses 
    print ("")
    print("---New Dictionary after Deleting---") 
    print ("")
    print(courses)

except Exception as ex:
    print(ex)

---Original Dictionary before Deleting---

---New Dictionary after Deleting---

{'0348-6642185': 'Adeeb', '0321-4971961': 'Saaliha', '0321-5865463': 'Kamaal', '0321-4582322': 'Naaila', '0323-7654151': 'Wajeeha'}

    print ("")

    courses.clear()
    print ("")
    print("---New Dictionary after Deleting---") 
    print ("")

    print(ex)

# Use pop() Function to remove specific element(s) of a Dictionary
    courses.popitem()
    print ("")
    print("---New Dictionary after Deleting---")

except Exception as ex:
    print(ex)

o Use  phone_directory  to  create  a  new  dictionary  which  contains numbers starting with 0321?
''' Purpose of Program 
The main purpose of the program is to create a new dictionary based on key-value pairs of an existing dictionary '''

try:
# Dictionary Initialization 
    print ("")
    phone_directory = {'0348-6642185': 'Adeeb', 
                        '0321-4971961':'Saaliha',
                        '0321-5865463': 'Kamaal', 
                        '0321-4582322': 'Naaila', 
                        '0345-8071517': 'Zuhra', 
                        '0323-7654151':'Wajeeha'}

    print("---Original Dictionary before Comprehension---")
    print ("")
    print(phone_directory) 

# Create a new dictionary with element of previous dictionary
    print ("")
    print("---New Dictionary After Comprehension---")
    print ("")
    new_phone_directory = {number: name for number, name in phone_directory.items() if number.startswith('0321')} 
    print(new_phone_directory)

except Exception as ex:
    print(ex)

---Original Dictionary before Comprehension---

{'0348-6642185': 'Adeeb', '0321-4971961': 'Saaliha', '0321-5865463': 'Kamaal', '0321-4582322': 'Naaila', '0345-8071517': 'Zuhra', '0323-7654151': 'Wajeeha'}

---New Dictionary After Comprehension---

{'0321-4971961': 'Saaliha', '0321-5865463': 'Kamaal', '0321-4582322': 'Naaila'}

''' Purpose of Program 
The main purpose of the program is to traversing a dictionary ''' 
# Initializing a Nested Dictionary i.e., student_courses

try:
    student_courses = { 'FA15-BCS-01': 
                   {'Program':'BS(CS)','Degree':'Bachelors in Computer Science'},
                   'FA15-BCS-03':
                   {'Program':'BS(CE)','Degree':'Bachelors in Computer Science'},
                   'FA15-BCS-05':
                   {'Program':'BS(CS)','Degree':'Bachelors in Computer Science'}}

# Traverse a Dictionary 
    for student_roll_no, program_details in student_courses.items(): 
        print("\nStudent_ID:", student_roll_no) 
        for key in program_details: 
            print(key + ':', program_details[key])

except:
    print("Error Occurred")

● Questions

o Pass Nested Dictionary to a Function (as shown in this Chapter)?
''' Purpose of Program 
The main purpose of the program is to Pass Nested Dictionary to a Function  '''
# Initializing a Nested Dictionary i.e., student_courses

try:

    student_courses = { 'FA15-BCS-01': 
                   [{'Program':'BS(CS)'}, {'Degree':'Bachelors in Computer Science'}],
                   'FA15-BCS-03': 
                   [{'Program':'BS(CE)'}, {'Degree':'Bachelors in Computer Science'}],
                   'FA15-BCS-05': [{'Program':'BS(CS)'}, {'Degree':'Bachelors in Computer Science'}]}

    def nested_dict_pairs_iterator(dict_obj): 
        # This function accepts a nested dictionary as argument and iterate over all values of nested dictionaries  
        # Iterate over all key-value pairs of dict argument 
        for key, value in dict_obj.items(): 
            print(key,value)
    if __name__ == '__main__':
        nested_dict_pairs_iterator(student_courses)
except Exception as ex:
    print(ex)

FA15-BCS-03 [{'Program': 'BS(CE)'}, {'Degree': 'Bachelors in Computer Science'}]

Your Turn Task 1

● Search and write down Linear and Non-linear Data Structures for the following Programming Languages?

o C
o Java
o React JS
o Ruby on Rail

Answer:

C

Linear Data Structures

o Array
o Linked List (Singly Linked List, Doubly Linked List)
o Queue
o Deque (Double-ended Queue)
o String (as a sequence of characters)

Non-Linear Data Structures

o Binary Tree
o Binary Search Tree (BST)
o Graph (using adjacency list or matrix)
o Heap
o Trie

Java

Linear Data Structures

o Array
o Linked List (Singly Linked List, Doubly Linked List)
o Stack
o Queue (Priority Queue, Deque)
o Vector

Non-Linear Data Structures

o TreeSet (Red-Black Tree)
o HashMap (Hash Table)
o TreeMap (Red-Black Tree)
o Binary Tree
o Trie

React JS

Linear Data Structures (JavaScript in React JS)

o Array
o Linked List (can be implemented in JavaScript)
o Stack (can be implemented using arrays)
o Queue (can be implemented using arrays)
o String (as a sequence of characters)

Non-Linear Data Structures (JavaScript in React JS)

o Object (similar to Hash Table)
o Map (ES6 Map)
o Set (ES6 Set)
o Tree (can be implemented in JavaScript)
o Graph (can be implemented in JavaScript)

Ruby on Rails

Linear Data Structures (Ruby) o Array o Linked List (can be implemented in Ruby) o Stack (can be implemented using arrays) o Queue (can be implemented using arrays) o String (as a sequence of characters)

Non-Linear Data Structures (Ruby)

o Hash (Hash Table)
o Set
o Tree (can be implemented in Ruby)
o Graph (can be implemented in Ruby)
o Heap (can be implemented in Ruby)
