● Consider three Strings (similar to the ones given in the TODO Task 1 of Lecture 17) and answer the questions given below.

● Questions

o Print String 1 using Single Quotes, String 2 using Double Quotes and String 3 using Triple Quotes

o Print lengths of String 1, String 2, and String 3 using len() Function
'''
Purpose of Program
The main purpose of the program is to create a string using single, double, and triple quotes and measure their lengths
'''

# Input + Processing + Output

try:
    
# Using Single Quotes
    print('---Message with Single Quotes---') 
    print('My name is Abdullah.')

# Using Double Quotes
    print("")
    print('---Message with Double Quotes---')
    print("My name is Abdullah. I study in Comsats University Lahore Campus.")

# Using Triple Quotes
    print("")
    print('---Message with Triple Quotes---') 
    print('''My name is Abdullah. 
    I study in Comsats University Lahore Campus.
    It is my Second Semester''')
    print("")

# Calculating Length of String with Single Quotes using len() Function
    print('---Length of String with Single Quotes---')
    print('Length of "My name is Abdullah." is: ', len("My name is Abdullah."))
    print("")

# Calculating Length of String with Double Quotes using len() Function
    print('---Length of String with Double Quotes---')
    print("My name is Abdullah. I study in Comsats University Lahore Campus.' is: ", len("My name is Abdullah. I study in Comsats University Lahore Campus."))
    print("")
                                                                                   
# Calculating Length of String with Triple Quotes using len() Function
    print('---Length of String with Triple Quotes---') 
    print('''Length of 'My name is Abdullah. 
    I study in Comsats University Lahore Campus.
    It is my Second Semester' is: ''', len("My name is Abdullah. I study in Comsats University Lahore Campus. It is my Second Semester"))
                                                                                   
except:
    print('Error Occurred')

Your Turn Task 3

● Consider a String (similar to the one given in the TODO Task 3 of Lecture 17) and answer the questions given below.

● Questions

o Apply following functions on String 1 and print the original and new string on the Output Screen?
    ▪ title()
    ▪ capitalize()
    ▪ upper()
    ▪ lower()
    ▪ center()
'''
Purpose of Program
The main purpose of the program is to format string using following built-in Functions i.e., 
title(), capitalize(), upper(), lower() and center()
'''

# Input + Processing + Output
try:

# Initialize a Message
    message = 'My name is Abdullah.'

# Using title() Function
    print('---Original String before using title() Function---')
    print(message)
    print("")

    print('---New String after using title() Function---')
    print(message.title())

# Using capitalize() Function
    print("")
    print('---Original String before using capitalize() Function---') 
    print(message)
    print("")

    print('---New String after using capitalize() Function---') 
    print(message.capitalize())

# Using upper() Function
    print("")
    print('---Original String before using upper() Function---') 
    print(message)
    print("")

    print('---New String after using upper() Function---') 
    print(message.upper())

# Using lower() Function
    print("")
    print('---Original String before using lower() Function---') 
    print(message)
    print("")

    print('---New String after using lower() Function---') 
    print(message.lower())

# Using center() Function
    print("")
    print('---Original String before using center() Function---') 
    print("Original Message: "+ message)
    print("")

    print('---New String after using center() Function---') 
    print(message.center(100))

except:
    print('Error Occurred')

Your Turn Task 4

● Consider a String (similar to the one given in the TODO Task 4 of Lecture 17) and answer the questions given below.

● Questions

o Apply following techniques to access elements of a String (as shown in this Chapter) on selected String and print the original and new string on the Output Screen?
    ▪ Indexing
    ▪ Slicing
    ▪ Splitting
''' Purpose of Program
The main purpose of the program is to access elements from a string using indexing,
slicing and split() function '''

# Input + Processing + Output

try:
    
# Initialize a Message
    message = 'My name is Abdullah.'

# Accessing Elements of a String using Indexing
    print("")
    print('---Original String before Indexing---') 
    print(message)
    print("")
    print('---New String after Indexing---')

# Access First Element of String
    print("Access Element at First Index i.e., message[0] is: "+ message[0])

# Access 14th Element of String
    print("Access Element at 14th Index i.e., message[14] is: "+ message[14])

# Access Last Element of String
    print("Access Element at last Index i.e., message[-1] is: "+ message[-1])

# Using Slicing
    print("")
    print('---Original String before Slicing---') 
    print(message)
    print("")
    print('---New String after Slicing---')

# Access First Sentence of String with stop value only i.e., [:13]
    print("Access First Sentence of String with stop value only i.e., [:13]: "+ message[:13])

# Access First Sentence of String with both start and stop value i.e., [0:13] 
    print("Access First Sentence of String with both start and stop value i.e.,[0:13]: "+ message[0:13])

# Access Middle Sentence of String
    print("Access Element from Middle Sentence i.e., message[14:53]: "+ message[14:53])

# Access Last Sentence of String with start value only i.e., message[55:]
    print("Access Last Sentence of String with start value only i.e., message[55:]: "+ message[55:])
    
# Access Last Sentence of String with both start and stop value i.e., [55:91] 
    print("Access Element from Last Sentence i.e.,message[55:91]: "+ message[55:91])

# Split String on basis of full stop (.) using split() Function
    print("")
    print('---Original String before using split() Function---') 
    print(message)
    print("")
    print('---New String after using split() Function---')
    print(message.split('.'))

# Split String on basis of spaces using split() Function 
    print("")
    print('---Original String before using split() Function---') 
    print(message)
    print("")
    print('---New String after using split() Function---') 
    print(message.split(' '))

except:
    print('Error Occurred')

● Consider a String (similar to the one given in the TODO Task 5 of Lecture 17) and answer the questions given below.

● Questions

o Apply following functions on String 1 and print the original and new string on the Output Screen?
    ▪strip()
    ▪ rstrip()
    ▪ lstrip()
'''
Purpose of Program
The main purpose of the program is to remove Whitespaces from a String using strip(), rstrip(), lstrip() Functions
'''

# Input + Processing + Output 
try:

# Initialize a Message
    message = ' My name is Abdullah. '

# Using strip() Function on message 
    print("")
    print('---Original String before using strip() Function---') 
    print(message)
    print("Length of Original String i.e., message: ",len(message))
    
    print("")
    print('---New String after using strip() Function---')
    print(message.strip())
    print("Length of New String i.e., message: ",len(message.strip()))
    
# Using rstrip() Function on message 
    print("") 
    print('---Original String i.e., message_1 before using rstrip() Function---') 
    print(message) 
    print("Length of Original Message i.e., message_1: ",len(message)) 
    
    print("") 
    print('---New String i.e., message_1 after using rstrip() Function---') 
    print(message.rstrip()) 
    print("Length of New Message: ",len(message.rstrip()))
    
# Using lstrip() Function on message_1
    print("")
    print('---Original String i.e., message_1 before using lstrip() Function---') 
    print(message)
    print("Length of Original Message i.e., message_1: ",len(message))
    
    print("") 
    print('---New String i.e., message_1 after using lrip() Function---') 
    print(message.lstrip())
    print("Length of New Message: ",len(message.lstrip()))

except: 
    print('Error Occurred')

numbers to string
'''

    number = 534
    string_number = '654'
    
# Using str() Function
    print("")

    print(number)
    print('Data Type of Number before Converting into String:') 
    print(type(number))
    print("")
    
    print('---New Number after Conversion into String---') 
    print(str(number))
    print('Data Type of Number after Converting into String') 
    print(type(str(number)))
    print("")
    
# Using int() Function
    print("")
    print('---Original String before Conversion into Number---') 
    print(string_number)
    print('Data Type of String before Converting into Number:')
    print(type(string_number))
    print("")
    
    print('---New String after Conversion into Number---')
    print(int(string_number))
    print('Data Type of String after Converting into Number:')
    print(type(int(string_number)))
    print("")
except:

● Consider a String (similar to the one given in the TODO Task 7 of Lecture 17) and answer the questions given below.

● Questions

o Apply following operators and functions to insert characters at: (1) start, (2) specific position, and (3) end of String 1 (as shown in this Chapter) and print the original and new string on the Output Screen?

    ▪ Concatenation Operator (+)
    ▪ join() Function
    ▪ Formatting Operator (%)
    ▪ format() Function
    ▪ F-String Prefix
    ▪ find() Function

1. Start

''' Purpose of Program
The main purpose of the program is to insert character at start of a string and display the result on the Output Screen '''

# Input + Processing + Output
try:
    
# Initialize Variable
    message = 'My name is Abdullah.'
    print('---Original String before using + Operator---')
    print(message)
    print("")

# Using + Operator to insert Element at First Index of a String 
    new_message = "*" + message[0:]
    print('---New String after using + Operator ---') 
    print(new_message)
    print("")

# Using join() Function to insert Element at First Index of a String
    print('---Original String before using join() Function---') 
    print(message)
    print("")
    newmessage = ''.join(("*",message))
    print('---New String after using join() Function---') 
    print(newmessage)
    print("")
    
# Using % Operator to insert Element at First Index of a String
    print('---Original String before using % Operator---') 
    print(message)
    print("")
    new_message = "%sMy name is Abdullah." %'*'
    print('---New String after using % Operator---')
    print(new_message)
    print("")
    
# Using format() Function to insert Element at First Index of a String
    print('---Original String before using format() Function---') 
    print(message)
    print("")
    new_message = "{}My name is Abdullah.".format('*')
    print('---New String after using format() Function---')
    print(new_message)
    print("")
    
# Using f Prefix to insert Element at First Index of a String
    print('---Original String before using f Prefix---') 
    print(message)
    print("")
    new_message = f"{'*'}My name is Abdullah."
    print('---New String after using f Prefix---') 
    print(new_message)
    print("")
    
# Using find() Function to insert Element at First Index of a String
    print('---Original String before using find() Function---') 
    print(message)
    print("")
    index = message.find('My')
    final_string = '*' + message[index:]
    print('---New String after using find() Function---') 
    print(final_string)
    print("")
# Using split(), join() and insert() Functions to insert Element at First Index of a String 
    print('---Original String before using split() Function---') 
    print(message)
    split_strings = message.split()
    split_strings.insert(0, '*') 
    updated_string = ' '.join(split_strings)
    print('---New String after using split() Function---') 
    print(updated_string)
except:
    print('Error Occurred')

''' Purpose of Program

# Input + Processing + Output
try:
    
# Initialize Variable
    message = 'My name is Abdullah.'
    print('---Original String before using + Operator---')
    print(message)
    print("")

# Using + Operator to insert Element at Last Index of a String 
    new_message = message[:0] + "*"
    print('---New String after using + Operator ---') 
    print(new_message)
    print("")
    
# Using join() Function to insert Element at Last Index of a String
    print("")
    print('---Original String before using join() Function---') 
    print(message)
    newmessage = ''.join((message,"*"))
    print('---New String after using join() Function---') 
    print(newmessage)
    print("")
    
# Using % Operator to insert Element at Last Index of a String
    print("")
    print('---Original String before using % Operator---') 
    print(message)
    new_message = "My name is Abdullah.%s" %'*'
    print('---New String after using % Operator---') 
    print(new_message)
    print("")

    print("")
    print('---Original String before using format() Function---')
    print(message)
    new_message = "My name is Abdullah.{}".format('*')
    print('---New String after using format() Function---') 
    print(new_message)
    print("")
    
# Using f Prefix to insert Element at Last Index of a String
    print("")
    print('---Original String before using f Prefix---') 
    print(message)
    new_message = f"My name is Abdullah.{'*'}"
    print('---New String after using f Prefix---') 
    print(new_message)
    print("")
    
# Using find() Function to insert Element at Last Index of a String
    print("")
    print('---Original String before using find() Function---')
    print(message)
    index = message.find('.')
    final_string = message[:index+1] + '*'
    print('---New String after using find() Function---') 
    print(final_string)
    print("")
    
# Using split(), join() and insert() Functions to insert Element at Last Index of a String 
    print('---Original String before using split() Function---') 
    print(message)
    split_strings = message.split()
    split_strings.insert((len(message) + 1), '*') 
    updated_string = ' '.join(split_strings)
    print('---New String after using split() Function---')
    print(updated_string)
    
except:
    print('Error Occurred')

Your Turn Task 8

● Consider a String (similar to the one given in the TODO Task 8 of Lecture 17) and answer the questions given below.

● Questions

o Traverse the selected String using the methods presented in this Chapter?

Method 1

''' Purpose of Program 
The main purpose of the program is to traverse an entire string and display the result on the Output Screen '''

# Input + Processing + Output
try: 
# Initialize Variable 
    message = 'Abdullah' 
# Traverse an entire String
    print(message) 
except: 
    print('Error Occurred')

Method 2

'''
Purpose of Program
The main purpose of the program is to traverse a string (element by element) and display the result 
on the Output Screen
'''

# Input + Processing + Output
try:
    
# ---Approach I - Iterate over a string (element by element) using for loop---
# Initialize Variable 
    message_1 = 'Abdullah'
# Iterate over a string (element by element) using for loop
    print(" ---Approach I - Iterate over a string (element by element) using for loop---")
    print("---Traverse a String (Element by Element) using for Loop---")
    for character in message_1:
        print(character)
# ---Approach II - Iterate over a string (element by element) using Indexing---

# Initialize Variable 
    message_2 = 'Abdullah'

# Iterate over a string (element by element) using for loop with Indexing
    print(" ---Approach II - Iterate over a string (element by element) using Indexing---")
    print("---Traverse a String (Element by Element) using for Loop with Indexing---")
    for element in range(0, len(message_2)):
        print("message_2[",element,"]: " + message_2[element])
        
# ---Approach III - Iterate over a string (element by element) using Slicing---
# Initialize Variable
    message_3 = 'Abdullah' 
    counter = 0
    print("---Approach III - Iterate over a string (element by element) using Slicing---")

# Iterate over a string (element by element) using for loop with Slicing
    print("---Traverse a String (Element by Element) using for Loop with Slicing--- ")
    
# Slicing Operator => string[starting index : ending index : step value] 
    for element in message_3[0 : len(message_3): 1]:
        counter = counter + 1 
        print("message_3[",counter,"]: " + element)
except:
    print('Error Occurred')
 ---Approach I - Iterate over a string (element by element) using for loop---
---Traverse a String (Element by Element) using for Loop---
A
b
d
u
l
l
a
h
 ---Approach II - Iterate over a string (element by element) using Indexing---
---Traverse a String (Element by Element) using for Loop with Indexing---

message_2[ 2 ]: d
message_2[ 3 ]: u
message_2[ 4 ]: l
message_2[ 5 ]: l
message_2[ 6 ]: a
message_2[ 7 ]: h
---Approach III - Iterate over a string (element by element) using Slicing---

● Consider a String (similar to the one given in the TODO Task 9 of Lecture 17) and answer the questions given below.

● Questions

o Apply methods presented in this Chapter to search the following elements in String 1
    ● name
    ● A
'''
Purpose of Program
The main purpose of the program is to search specific character from a string and display the 
result on the Output Screen
'''

# Input + Processing + Output
try:
    
# Initialize Variable
    message = 'My name is Abdullah' 
    print('---Original String before using find() Function---') 
    print(message)
    print("")
    
# Using find() Function to Search a Word from a String 
    index_of_character = message.find('name') 
    print('---Index of Searched Term (name) returned by Search Function---') 
    print(index_of_character) 
    print("") 

# Using find() Function to Search a Character from a String 
    print('---Original String before using find() Function---') 
    print(message) 
    print("")
    index_of_character = message.find('A') 
    print('Searching all instances of a Search Term (A)') 
    print(index_of_character) 
    print("") 

# Using split() and find() Function to Search a String using for Loop 
    split_message = message.split() 
    for elem in split_message: 
        index = elem.find("Abdullah") 
        if index != -1: 
            print(elem) 
except: 
    print('Error Occurred')

3

---Original String before using find() Function---
My name is Abdullah

Method 1

'''
Purpose of Program
The main purpose of the program is to sort the string in ascending order and display the result on 
the Output Screen
'''

# Input + Processing + Output
try:
    
# Approach I - sorted() Function to arrange string in Ascending Order
    
# Initialize Variable 
    message = 'My name is Abdullah'
    print('---Approach I - sorted() Function to arrange string in Ascending Order---') 
    print('')
    print('---Original String before using sorted() Function---')
    print(message)
    print('')
    
# Using sorted() Function to arrange string in Ascending Order
    messages = sorted(message, reverse=False)
    print('---New String after using sorted() Function---') 
    print(messages)
    print('')
# Approach II – sorted() and split() Function to arrange string in Ascending Order
    print('---Approach II - sorted() and split() Function to arrange string in Ascending Order---')
    print('')
# Using sorted() and split() Function to arrange string in Ascending Order messages = 
    sorted(message.split(' '),reverse = False)
    print('---New String after using sorted() Function---') 
    print(messages)
except:
    print('Error Occurred')

'''
Purpose of Program
The main purpose of the program is to access element(s) of a list using slicing and display the 
result on the output screen
'''
try:
# Initialize List 
    fruits = ['Mango','Orange','Banana','Apple','Grapes']
    ages = [25, 30, 15, 20, 22, 33]
    
# Access Element(s) of First List using Slicing
    print("---Access Element(s) of First List using Slicing---")
    print("")
    print("fruits[2:4]:",fruits[2:4])
    print("")

# Access from 2nd element till 4th element
    print("fruits[1:4]:", fruits[1:4])
    print("")

# Access from start till 3rd element 
    print("fruits[:3]:", fruits[:3])
    print("")

# Access from 2nd element till end
    print("fruits[1:]:", fruits[1:])
    print("")

# Access from start till 3rd last element 
    print("fruits[:-2]:", fruits[:-2]) 
    print("")

# Access from 3rd last element till 1st last element 
    print("fruits[-3:-1]:", fruits[-3:-1]) 
    print("")

# Access from 2nd element till 2nd last element
    print("fruits[1:-1]:", fruits[1:-1])
    print("")

# Access all elements 
    print("fruits[:]:",fruits[:]) 
    print("")
    
# Access Element(s) of Second List using Slicing
    print("---Access Element(s) of Second List using Slicing---")
    print("")
    print("ages[2:4]:",ages[2:4])
    print("")

# Access from 2nd element till 4th element
    print("ages[1:4]:", ages[1:4])
    print("")

# Access from start till 3rd element 
    print("ages[:3]:", ages[:3])
    print("")

# Access from 2nd element till end
    print("ages[1:]:", ages[1:])
    print("")

# Access from start till 3rd last element 
    print("ages[:-2]:", ages[:-2]) 
    print("")

# Access from 3rd last element till 1st last element 
    print("ages[-3:-1]:", ages[-3:-1]) 
    print("")

# Access from 2nd element till 2nd last element
    print("ages[1:-1]:", ages[1:-1])
    print("")

# Access all elements 
    print("ages[:]:",ages[:]) 
    print("")

except: 
    print("Error Occurred")

● Questions

o Traverse selected lists using following methods (as shown in this Chapter)
    ▪ Method 1: Traversing an Entire List
    ▪ Method 2: Traversing a List (Element by Element)

Method 1

'''
Purpose of Program
The main purpose of the program is to traverse an entire list and display the result on the Output 
Screen
'''

try:
    
# List Initialization
    fruits = ['Mango','Orange','Banana','Apple','Grapes']
    ages = [25, 30, 15, 20, 22, 33]

# Traverse an entire list
    print(fruits) 
    print("")
    print(ages)
except:
    print('Error Occurred')

Method 2

'''
Purpose of Program
The main purpose of the program is to traverse a list (element by element) and display the result 
on the Output Screen
'''

try:
# Iterate over First List (element by element) using for loop---

# List Initialization
    fruits = ['Mango','Orange','Banana','Apple','Grapes']
    ages = [25, 30, 15, 20, 22, 33]

# Iterate over First List (element by element) using for loop
    print("Iterate over First List (element by element) using for loop---")
    print("")
    print("---Traverse First List (Element by Element) using for Loop---")
    print("")
    for element in fruits:
        print (element)
    print("")
    
# Iterate over Second List (element by element) using for loop
    print("Iterate over Second List (element by element) using for loop---")
    print("")
    print("---Traverse Second List (Element by Element) using for Loop---")
    print("")
    for element in ages:
        print (element)
except:
    print('Error Occurred')

Purpose of Program
the main purpose of the program is to search a specific element from a list '''

# Approach I – Using in Operator to Search Element in First List

try:
# Initialize List
    fruits = ['Mango','Orange','Banana','Apple','Grapes']
    ages = [25, 30, 15, 20, 22, 33]

    print("Using in Operator to Search Element in First List")
    print("")
    element = 'Orange'

# Using in operator to Search Element in First List 
    if element in fruits:
        print(element + " is in List") 
        print("")
    else:
        print(element + " is not in List")
        print("")
        
    print("Using in Operator to Search Element in Second List")
    print("")
    element = 15

# Using in operator to Search Element in Second List 
    if element in ages:
        print(element, "is in List") 
        print("")
    else:
        print(element, "is not in List")
        print("")
except:
    print('Error Occurred')

Purpose of Program

    print("")
    
    print('---Original Second List before using sort() Function---')
    print("")
    print(ages)
    print("")

    print("")

Your Turn Task 7

● Consider two Lists (similar to the ones given in TODO Task 7 of Lecture 18) and answer the questions given below

● Questions

o Merge Elements of the selected lists using following methods (as shown in this Chapter)
    ▪   Method 1: Concatenate Lists using + Operator
    ▪   Method 2: Concatenate Lists using * Operator
    ▪   Method 3: Merge Lists using append() Function
    ▪   Method 4: Merge Lists using extend() Function

Method 1

'''
Purpose of Program
The main purpose of the program is to concatenate lists using + operator '''
try:
# Initialize List
    fruits = ['Mango','Orange','Banana','Apple','Grapes']
    ages = [25, 30, 15, 20, 22, 33]
    
    print('---Original Lists before Merging---')
    print("")
    print(fruits)
    print("")
    print(ages)
    print("")
    
# Using + Operator to Concatenate Lists 
    print('---New List after Merging---') 
    for count in range(len(fruits)):
        Merge_fruits_ages = fruits[count] + " - " + str(ages[count]) 
        print(Merge_fruits_ages)    

except:
    print('Error Occurred')

Method 2

'''
Purpose of Program
The main purpose of the program is to concatenate lists using * operator '''
try:
# Initialize List
    fruits = ['Mango','Orange','Banana','Apple','Grapes']    
    ages = [25, 30, 15, 20, 22, 33]   
    print('---Original Lists before Merging---')
    print("")
    print(fruits)
    print("")
    print(ages)
    print("")
    
# Using * Operator to Concatenate Lists 
    print('---New List after Merging---') 
    for count in range(len(fruits)):
        Merge_fruits_ages = [*(fruits[count],ages[count] )] 
        print(Merge_fruits_ages)    

except:
    print('Error Occurred')

Method 3

'''
Purpose of Program
The main purpose of the program is to concatenate lists using append () Function '''
try:
# Initialize List
    fruits = ['Mango','Orange','Banana','Apple','Grapes']
    ages = [25, 30, 15, 20, 22, 33]
    
    print('---Original Lists before Merging---')
    print("")
    print(fruits)
    print("")
    print(ages)
    print("")
    
# Using append () Function to Concatenate Lists 
    print('---New List after Merging---') 
    for element in ages:
        fruits.append(element) 
    print(fruits)    

except:
    print('Error Occurred')

Method 4

'''
Purpose of Program
The main purpose of the program is to concatenate lists using extend () Function '''
try:
# Initialize List
    fruits = ['Mango','Orange','Banana','Apple','Grapes']
    ages = [25, 30, 15, 20, 22, 33]
    
    print('---Original Lists before Merging---')
    print("")
    print(fruits)
    print("")
    print(ages)
    print("")
    
# Using extend () Function to Concatenate Lists 
    print('---New List after Merging---') 
    print("")
    fruits.extend(ages)
    print(fruits)    

except:
    print('Error Occurred')

    fruits = ['Mango','Guava','Grapefruit','Apple','Grapes']

    list_comprehension = [element for element in fruits if "G" in element]

    print("")

    ages = [25, 18, 15, 20, 22, 33]

    2, ['BK002', '1984', 'George Orwell', 'Dystopian', 'Political Fiction'],
    3, ['BK003', 'Moby Dick', 'Herman Melville', 'Adventure'],
    4, ['BK004', 'The Great Gatsby', 'F. Scott Fitzgerald', 'Fiction'],

]

    print("")

    print("")

    library_books[2][0] = 'BK002'

    library_books[3] = 1 
    library_books[4][0] = 'BK001' 
    library_books[4][1] = 'Brave New World'

Your Turn Task 12

● Consider two Lists (similar to the ones given in TODO Task 12 of Lecture 18) and answer the questions given below

● Questions

o Implement  the  concept  of  Lambda Function  using  the  following methos dicussed in this Chapter
    ▪   Method 1: Use filter() Function
    ▪   Method 2: Use map() Function

Method 1

''' Purpose of Program 
The main purpose of program is to filter only the cars with 'M' letter from the List and prime numbers less than 10'''

try: 
# List Initiazation 
    fruits = ['Mango','Guava','Grapefruit','Apple','Grapes']
    ages = [25, 30, 15, 20, 22, 33]
    print("---Origninal Lists before using filter() Function---")
    print("")
    print(fruits)
    print("")
    print(ages)
    
# Lists after using filter() Function 
    print("")
    fruits_with_G = list(filter(lambda fruit: 'G' in fruit, fruits))
    print("---New Lists after using filter() Function---") 
    print('')
    print(fruits_with_G)
    print('')
    
    updated_ages = list(filter(lambda number: number < 25, ages))
    print("---New List after using filter() Function---") 
    print('')
    print(updated_ages)
except: 
    print("Error Occurred")
---Origninal Lists before using filter() Function---

['Mango', 'Guava', 'Grapefruit', 'Apple', 'Grapes']

[25, 30, 15, 20, 22, 33]

---New Lists after using filter() Function---

['Guava', 'Grapefruit', 'Grapes']

---New List after using filter() Function---

[15, 20, 22]

Method 2

''' Purpose of Program 
The main purpose of program is to add a specific number each item in a list using map() '''

try: 
# List Initiazation 
    fruits = ['Mango','Orange','Banana','Apple','Grapes']
    ages = [25, 30, 15, 20, 22, 33]
    print("---Origninal Lists before using map() Function---")
    print("")
    print(fruits)
    print("")
    print(ages)
    
# Lists after using filter() Function 
    print("")
    updated_fruits = list(map(lambda fruit: fruit.upper(), fruits))
    print("---New Lists after using map() Function---") 
    print('')
    print(updated_fruits)
    print('')
    
    updated_ages = list(map(lambda number: number + 10, ages))
    print("---New List after using map() Function---") 
    print('')
    print(updated_ages)
except: 
    print("Error Occurred")
---Origninal Lists before using map() Function---

['Mango', 'Orange', 'Banana', 'Apple', 'Grapes']

[25, 30, 15, 20, 22, 33]

---New Lists after using map() Function---

['MANGO', 'ORANGE', 'BANANA', 'APPLE', 'GRAPES']

---New List after using map() Function---

[35, 40, 25, 30, 32, 43]

''' Purpose of Program 
The main purpose of the program is to pass lists to a function and display the result on the Output Screen '''
def list_function(list): 
    for element in list:
        print(element) 
        
if __name__ == "__main__": # main() Function 
    try: # Initializing a List 
        fruits = ['Mango','Orange','Banana','Apple','Grapes'] # Function Call 
        print("---Available Cars are---")
        print("")
        list_function(fruits) 
        print("")
        
# Initializing a Nested List 
        library_books = [
    ['Book ID', 'Title', 'Author', 'Genre'],
    1, ['BK001', 'To Kill a Mockingbird', 'Harper Lee', 'Fiction'],
    2, ['BK002', '1984', 'George Orwell', 'Dystopian', 'Political Fiction'],

    4, ['BK004', 'The Great Gatsby', 'F. Scott Fitzgerald', 'Fiction'],
    5, ['BK005', 'War and Peace', 'Leo Tolstoy', 'Historical Fiction', 'Epic']
]
        print("---Studends Enrolled---")
        list_function(library_books) 
    
    except ValueError: 
        print("Error! Enter Valid Values")

''' Purpose of Program 
The main purpose of the program is to initialize a complete dictionary and display its content (data values) on the Output Screen '''
try:
# Dictionary Initialization - Method 1: Use {} 
    print("---Dictionary Initialization - Use {}---")
    print ("")
    employee_directory = {
    'E001': 'John Doe',
    'E002': 'Jane Smith',
    'E003': 'Emily Davis',
    'E004': 'Michael Brown',
    'E005': 'Laura Wilson',
    'E006': 'David Johnson'
}
    
# Display Data Values of a Dictionary
    print ("")
    print("Data Values of phone_directory:", employee_directory)
    
# Display Length of a Dictionary using len() Function
    print ("")
    print("Length of phone_directory:", len(employee_directory))
    
# Display Type of a Dictionary using type() Function
    print ("")
    print("Data-Type of phone_directory:", type(employee_directory)) 


# Dictionary Initialization - Method 2: Use dict() Function 
    print ("")
    print("---Dictionary Initialization – Use dict() Function---")
    print ("")
    student_enrollments = {
    'Mathematics': ['Alice', 'Bob', 'Charlie', 'David', 'Eve'],
    'Physics': ['Alice', 'Bob', 'Eve'],
    'Chemistry': ['Charlie', 'David', 'Frank'],
    'Biology': ['Alice', 'David', 'Eve', 'Grace'],
    'Computer Science': ['Bob', 'Charlie', 'Frank', 'Grace']
}
    
# Display Data Values of a Dictionary
    print ("")
    print("Data Values of courses:", student_enrollments)

# Display Length of a Dictionary using len() Function
    print ("")
    print("Length of tomb_of_sahaba_2:",len(student_enrollments))

# Display Type of a Dictionary using type() Function 
    print ("")
    print("Data-Type of tomb_of_sahaba_2:",type(student_enrollments))


except: 
    print("Error Occurred")

try:
# Dictionary Initialization 
    print ("")
    employee_directory = {
    'E001': 'John Doe',
    'E002': 'Jane Smith',
    'E003': 'Emily Davis',

    print("")

    print("---Data Type of i.e., phone_directory after converting to List---") 
    print("")
    print(type(list_employee_directory))

    print("")

# Display Updated Dictionary after Adding Element at Start of a Dictionary 
    print("")
    print("---Updated Dictionary after Adding Element at Start of a Dictionary---") 
    print("")
    print(list_employee_directory)

    print ("")
    student_enrollments = {
    'Mathematics': ['Alice', 'Bob', 'Charlie', 'David', 'Eve'],
    'Physics': ['Alice', 'Bob', 'Eve'],
    'Chemistry': ['Charlie', 'David', 'Frank'],
}
    
    print("---Original Dictionary before Adding Element at Desired Location of a Dictionary---") 
    print("")
    print(student_enrollments)
    
# Data Type of i.e., courses before converting to List
    print("")
    print("---Data Type of i.e., courses before converting to List---") 
    print("")
    print(type(student_enrollments)) 
    
# Converting a Dictionary into a List and store list in "list_courses" 
    print("")
    list_student_enrollments = list(student_enrollments.items()) 
    
# Data Type of i.e., courses after converting to List 
    print("")
    print("---Data Type of i.e., courses after converting to List---") 
    print("")
    print(type(list_student_enrollments))
    
# Add Data Value at Start of a Dictionary using insert() Function 
    print("")
    list_student_enrollments.insert(2,('Biology',['Alice', 'David', 'Eve', 'Grace']))

# Display Updated Dictionary after Adding Element at Desired Location of a Dictionary 
    print("")
    print("---Updated Dictionary after Adding Element at Desired Location of a Dictionary---") 
    print("")
    print(list_student_enrollments)

except: 
    print("Error Occurred")

Method 2

''' Purpose of Program 
The main purpose of the program is to search element(s) using value '''

try:
# Dictionary Initialization 
    print ("")
    employee_directory = {
    'E001': 'John Doe',
    'E002': 'Jane Smith',
    'E003': 'Emily Davis',
    'E004': 'Michael Brown',
    'E005': 'Laura Wilson',
    'E006': 'David Johnson'
}
    

    print("---Using Keys(), Values() and index()---")
    print("")

# Store all Keys from the Dictionary in the Variable i.e., key_list 
    key_list = list(employee_directory.keys())
    print("Keys in the Dictionary:", key_list)
    print("")

# Store all Values from the Dictionary in the Variable i.e., val_list 
    val_list = list(employee_directory.values())
    print("Values in the Dictionary:", val_list)
    print("")

    print("---------------------------------------------------------")
    print("")
# Store Index of Value 'Kamaal' in a Variable i.e., position 
    position_John_Doe = val_list.index('John Doe')
# Display the Key with Value 'John Doe'
    print("Key against Value 'John Doe':",key_list[position_John_Doe])
    print("")

# Dictionary Initialization 
    print ("")
    student_enrollments = {
    'Mathematics': ['Alice', 'Bob', 'Charlie', 'David', 'Eve'],
    'Physics': ['Alice', 'Bob', 'Eve'],
    'Chemistry': ['Charlie', 'David', 'Frank'],
}
    
    print("---Using Keys(), Values() and index()---")
    print("")

# Store all Keys from the Dictionary in the Variable i.e., key_list 
    key_list = list(student_enrollments.keys())
    print("Keys in the Dictionary:", key_list)
    print("")

# Store all Values from the Dictionary in the Variable i.e., val_list 
    val_list = list(student_enrollments.values())
    print("Values in the Dictionary:", val_list)
    print("")

    print("---------------------------------------------------------")
    print("")
# Store Index of Value ['Alice', 'Bob', 'Eve'] in a Variable i.e., position 
    position = val_list.index(['Alice', 'Bob', 'Eve'])
# Display the Key with Value ['Alice', 'Bob', 'Eve']
    print("Key against Value ['Alice', 'Bob', 'Eve']:",key_list[position])
    print("")
except: 
    print("Error Occurred")

The main purpose of the program is to sort a dictionary by key-value pair '''
try:
# Dictionary Initialization 
    print ("")

    'E003': 'Emily Davis',

    dict_employee_directory = employee_directory.items()

    print("---New Dictionary after Sorting---") 
    print ("")

Method 3.1

''' Purpose of Program 
The main purpose of the program is to sorting a dictionary by value in descending order '''
try:
# Dictionary Initialization 
    print ("")
    employee_directory = {
    'E001': 'John Doe',
    'E002': 'Jane Smith',
    'E003': 'Emily Davis',
    'E004': 'Michael Brown',
    'E005': 'Laura Wilson',
    'E006': 'David Johnson'
}
    
# Sort Dictionary using 'get'
    print("---Sort Dictionary using 'get'---") 
    print ("")
    print("---Original Dictionary before Sorting---")
    print ("")
    print(employee_directory)
    print ("")
    print("---New Dictionary after Sorting---")
    print ("")
    for elements in sorted(employee_directory, key = employee_directory.get, reverse = False):
        print(elements, employee_directory[elements])
     
# Dictionary Initialization 
    print ("")
    student_enrollments = {
    'Mathematics': ['Alice', 'Bob', 'Charlie', 'David', 'Eve'],
    'Physics': ['Alice', 'Bob', 'Eve'],
    'Chemistry': ['Charlie', 'David', 'Frank'],
}
    
# Sort Dictionary using 'get'
    print("---Sort Dictionary using 'get'---") 
    print ("")
    print("---Original Dictionary before Sorting---")
    print ("")
    print(student_enrollments)
    print ("")
    print("---New Dictionary after Sorting---")
    print ("")
    for elements in sorted(student_enrollments, key = student_enrollments.get, reverse = False):
        print(elements, student_enrollments[elements])

except: 
    print("Error Occurred")

---Sort Dictionary using 'get'---

---Original Dictionary before Sorting---

---New Dictionary after Sorting---

E002 Jane Smith
E001 John Doe
E005 Laura Wilson
E004 Michael Brown

---Sort Dictionary using 'get'---

---Original Dictionary before Sorting---

---New Dictionary after Sorting---

Physics ['Alice', 'Bob', 'Eve']
Chemistry ['Charlie', 'David', 'Frank']

Your Turn Task 7

● Consider two Dictionaries (similar to the ones given in TODO Task 7 of Lecture 19) and answer the questions given below

● Questions

o Merge the selected Dictionaries using following methods (as shown in this Chapter)
    ▪   Method 1: Concatenate Dictionaries using update() Function
    ▪   Method 2: Concatenate Dictionaries using ** Operators

Method 1

''' Purpose of Program 
The main purpose of the program is to concatenate dictionaries using update() function '''
try:
# Dictionary Initialization 
    print ("")
    employee_directory = {
    'E001': 'John Doe',
    'E002': 'Jane Smith',
    'E003': 'Emily Davis',
    'E004': 'Michael Brown',
    'E005': 'Laura Wilson',
    'E006': 'David Johnson'
}
    student_enrollments = {
    'Mathematics': ['Alice', 'Bob', 'Charlie', 'David', 'Eve'],
    'Physics': ['Alice', 'Bob', 'Eve'],
    'Chemistry': ['Charlie', 'David', 'Frank'],
}
    
    print("---Original Dictionary before Merge---")
    print ("\nDictionary 1\n")
    print(employee_directory)
    print ("\nDictionary 2\n")
    print(student_enrollments)
    print ("")

# Use update() Function to merge two Dictionaries
    employee_directory.update(student_enrollments) 
    print("---New Dictionary after Merge---") 
    print ("")
    print(employee_directory)

except: 
    print("Error Occurred")

Method 2

''' Purpose of Program 
The main purpose of the program is to concatenate dictionaries using ** operator '''
try:
# Dictionary Initialization 
    print ("")
    employee_directory = {
    'E001': 'John Doe',
    'E002': 'Jane Smith',
    'E003': 'Emily Davis',
    'E004': 'Michael Brown',
    'E005': 'Laura Wilson',
    'E006': 'David Johnson'
}
    student_enrollments = {
    'Mathematics': ['Alice', 'Bob', 'Charlie', 'David', 'Eve'],
    'Physics': ['Alice', 'Bob', 'Eve'],
    'Chemistry': ['Charlie', 'David', 'Frank'],
}
    
    print("---Original Dictionary before Merge---")
    print ("\nDictionary 1\n")
    print(employee_directory)
    print ("\nDictionary 2\n")
    print(student_enrollments)
    print ("")

# Use ** operator to merge two Dictionaries
    dict3_employee_directory = dict(employee_directory,** student_enrollments) 
    print("---New Dictionary after Merge---") 
    print ("")
    print(dict3_employee_directory)

except: 
    print("Error Occurred")

---Original Dictionary before Merge---

Dictionary 1

{'E001': 'John Doe', 'E002': 'Jane Smith', 'E003': 'Emily Davis', 'E004': 'Michael Brown', 'E005': 'Laura Wilson', 'E006': 'David Johnson'}

Dictionary 2

{'Mathematics': ['Alice', 'Bob', 'Charlie', 'David', 'Eve'], 'Physics': ['Alice', 'Bob', 'Eve'], 'Chemistry': ['Charlie', 'David', 'Frank']}

---New Dictionary after Merge---

{'E001': 'John Doe', 'E002': 'Jane Smith', 'E003': 'Emily Davis', 'E004': 'Michael Brown', 'E005': 'Laura Wilson', 'E006': 'David Johnson', 'Mathematics': ['Alice', 'Bob', 'Charlie', 'David', 'Eve'], 'Physics': ['Alice', 'Bob', 'Eve'], 'Chemistry': ['Charlie', 'David', 'Frank']}

Your Turn Task 8

● Consider two Dictionaries (similar to the ones given in TODO Task 8 of Lecture 19) and answer the questions given below

● Questions

o Update the selected Dictionaries using following methods (as shown in this Chapter)
    ▪   Method 1: Update the key of a Dictionary using pop() Function
    ▪   Method 2: Update the value of a Dictionary
    ▪   Method 3: Update the value of a Dictionary using update() Function

Method 1

''' Purpose of Program 
The main purpose of the program is to update the key of a dictionary using pop() function '''
try:
# Dictionary Initialization 
    print ("")
    employee_directory = {
    'E001': 'John Doe',
    'E002': 'Jane Smith',
    'E003': 'Emily Davis',
    'E004': 'Michael Brown',
    'E005': 'Laura Wilson',
    'E006': 'David Johnson'
}
    
    print("---Original Dictionary before Updatation---")
    print ("")
    print(employee_directory)
    print ("")
    
# Use pop() Function to update old_key_value with new_key_value 
    new_key = "E009" 
    old_key = "E001" 
    employee_directory[new_key] = employee_directory.pop(old_key)
    print("---New Dictionary after Updatation---") 
    print(employee_directory)

    student_enrollments = {
    'Mathematics': ['Alice', 'Bob', 'Charlie', 'David', 'Eve'],
    'Physics': ['Alice', 'Bob', 'Eve'],
    'Chemistry': ['Charlie', 'David', 'Frank'],
}
    
    print("---Original Dictionary before Updatation---")
    print ("")
    print(student_enrollments)
    print ("")
    
# Use pop() Function to update old_key_value with new_key_value 
    new_key = "Biology" 
    old_key = "Physics" 
    student_enrollments[new_key] = student_enrollments.pop(old_key)
    print("---New Dictionary after Updatation---") 
    print(student_enrollments)

except: 
    print("Error Occurred")

---Original Dictionary before Updatation---

{'E001': 'John Doe', 'E002': 'Jane Smith', 'E003': 'Emily Davis', 'E004': 'Michael Brown', 'E005': 'Laura Wilson', 'E006': 'David Johnson'}

---New Dictionary after Updatation---
{'E002': 'Jane Smith', 'E003': 'Emily Davis', 'E004': 'Michael Brown', 'E005': 'Laura Wilson', 'E006': 'David Johnson', 'E009': 'John Doe'}
---Original Dictionary before Updatation---

{'Mathematics': ['Alice', 'Bob', 'Charlie', 'David', 'Eve'], 'Physics': ['Alice', 'Bob', 'Eve'], 'Chemistry': ['Charlie', 'David', 'Frank']}

---New Dictionary after Updatation---
{'Mathematics': ['Alice', 'Bob', 'Charlie', 'David', 'Eve'], 'Chemistry': ['Charlie', 'David', 'Frank'], 'Biology': ['Alice', 'Bob', 'Eve']}

Method 2

''' Purpose of Program 
The main purpose of the program is to update the value of a dictionary '''
try:
# Dictionary Initialization 
    print ("")
    employee_directory = {
    'E001': 'John Doe',
    'E002': 'Jane Smith',
    'E003': 'Emily Davis',
    'E004': 'Michael Brown',
    'E005': 'Laura Wilson',
    'E006': 'David Johnson'
}
    
    print("---Original Dictionary before Updatation---")
    print ("")
    print(employee_directory)
    print ("")
    
# Use key for updating value in a Dictionary 
    employee_directory["E001"] = "Robert Brown"
    print("---New Dictionary after Updatation---") 
    print ("")
    print(employee_directory)
    print ("")
    
    student_enrollments = {
    'Mathematics': ['Alice', 'Bob', 'Charlie', 'David', 'Eve'],
    'Physics': ['Alice', 'Bob', 'Eve'],
    'Chemistry': ['Charlie', 'David', 'Frank'],
}

    print("---Original Dictionary before Updatation---")
    print ("")
    print(student_enrollments)
    print ("")
    
# Use key for updating value in a Dictionary 
    student_enrollments["Physics"] = "['Alice', 'Bob', 'Eve','Morgan','Tony']"
    print("---New Dictionary after Updatation---") 
    print ("")
    print(student_enrollments)
    print ("")

except: 
    print("Error Occurred")

---Original Dictionary before Updatation---

{'E001': 'John Doe', 'E002': 'Jane Smith', 'E003': 'Emily Davis', 'E004': 'Michael Brown', 'E005': 'Laura Wilson', 'E006': 'David Johnson'}

---New Dictionary after Updatation---

{'E001': 'Robert Brown', 'E002': 'Jane Smith', 'E003': 'Emily Davis', 'E004': 'Michael Brown', 'E005': 'Laura Wilson', 'E006': 'David Johnson'}

---Original Dictionary before Updatation---

{'Mathematics': ['Alice', 'Bob', 'Charlie', 'David', 'Eve'], 'Physics': ['Alice', 'Bob', 'Eve'], 'Chemistry': ['Charlie', 'David', 'Frank']}

---New Dictionary after Updatation---

Method 3

''' Purpose of Program
The main purpose of the program is to update the value of a dictionary using update() function '''

try:
# Dictionary Initialization 
    print ("")
    employee_directory = {
    'E001': 'John Doe',
    'E002': 'Jane Smith',
    'E003': 'Emily Davis',
    'E004': 'Michael Brown',
    'E005': 'Laura Wilson',
    'E006': 'David Johnson'
}
    
    print("---Original Dictionary before Updatation---")
    print ("")
    print(employee_directory)
    print ("")
    
# Use update() Function for updating value of a Dictionay
    employee_directory.update({'E003': 'Robert Brown'})
    print("---New Dictionary after Updatation---") 
    print ("")
    print(employee_directory)
    print ("")
    
    student_enrollments = {
    'Mathematics': ['Alice', 'Bob', 'Charlie', 'David', 'Eve'],
    'Physics': ['Alice', 'Bob', 'Eve'],
    'Chemistry': ['Charlie', 'David', 'Frank'],
}
    print("---Original Dictionary before Updatation---")
    print ("")
    print(student_enrollments)
    print ("")
    
# Use update() Function for updating value of a Dictionay
    student_enrollments.update({'Chemistry': ['Alice', 'David', 'Eve', 'Grace']})
    print("---New Dictionary after Updatation---") 
    print ("")
    print(student_enrollments)
    print ("")

except: 
    print("Error Occurred")

Your Turn Task 10

● Consider a Dictionary (similar to the one given in TODO Task 10 of Lecture 19) and answer the questions given below

● Questions

o Use  the  concept  of  Dictionary  Comprehension  to  create  a  new Dictionary based on the selected Dictionary?
''' Purpose of Program 
The main purpose of the program is to create a new dictionary based on key-value pairs of an existing dictionary '''

try:
# Dictionary Initialization 
    print ("")
    employee_directory = {
    'E001': 'John Doe',
    'E002': 'Jane Smith',
    'E003': 'Emily Davis',
    'E004': 'Michael Brown',
    'E005': 'Laura Wilson',
    'E006': 'David Johnson'
}

    print("---Original Dictionary before Comprehension---")
    print ("")
    print(employee_directory) 

# Create a new dictionary with element of previous dictionary
    print ("")
    print("---New Dictionary After Comprehension---")
    print ("")
    new_employee_directory = {number: name for number, name in employee_directory.items() if name.startswith('J')} 
    print(new_employee_directory)

except Exception as ex:
    print(ex)

---Original Dictionary before Comprehension---

{'E001': 'John Doe', 'E002': 'Jane Smith', 'E003': 'Emily Davis', 'E004': 'Michael Brown', 'E005': 'Laura Wilson', 'E006': 'David Johnson'}

---New Dictionary After Comprehension---

{'E001': 'John Doe', 'E002': 'Jane Smith'}

    print("Data-Type of students:", type(vehicle_information))
    print("")

    print("Length of students:", len(vehicle_information))
    print("")
    
except:
    print("Error Occurred")

Operation 4

''' Purpose of Program 
The main purpose of the program is to traversing a dictionary ''' 
# Initializing a Nested Dictionary i.e., vehicle_information

try:
    vehicle_information = {
    'VEH001': {'Make': 'Toyota', 'Model': 'Corolla', 'Year': 2020},
    'VEH002': {'Make': 'Honda', 'Model': 'Civic', 'Year': 2018},
    'VEH003': {'Make': 'Ford', 'Model': 'Mustang', 'Year': 2021}
}

# Traverse a Dictionary 
    for vehicle_id, vehicle_details in vehicle_information.items(): 
        print("\nVehicle ID:", vehicle_id) 
        for key in vehicle_details: 
            print(key + ':', vehicle_details[key])

except:
    print("Error Occurred")

Year: 2018

Your Turn Task 13

● Consider a Nested Dictionary (similar to the one given in TODO Task 1 of Lecture 19) and answer the questions given below

● Questions

o Pass Nested Dictionary to a Function (as shown in this Chapter)?
''' Purpose of Program 
The main purpose of the program is to Pass Nested Dictionary to a Function  '''
# Initializing a Nested Dictionary i.e., student_courses

try:

vehicle_registration = {
    'VEH-1234': [{'Make': 'Toyota'}, {'Model': 'Corolla'}, {'Year': '2020'}, {'Color': 'White'}],
    'VEH-5678': [{'Make': 'Honda'}, {'Model': 'Civic'}, {'Year': '2018'}, {'Color': 'Black'}],
    'VEH-9101': [{'Make': 'Ford'}, {'Model': 'Mustang'}, {'Year': '2021'}, {'Color': 'Red'}],
    'VEH-1121': [{'Make': 'Chevrolet'}, {'Model': 'Camaro'}, {'Year': '2019'}, {'Color': 'Blue'}],
    'VEH-3141': [{'Make': 'Tesla'}, {'Model': 'Model 3'}, {'Year': '2022'}, {'Color': 'Silver'}]
}
    def nested_dict_pairs_iterator(dict_obj): 
        # This function accepts a nested dictionary as argument and iterate over all values of nested dictionaries  
        # Iterate over all key-value pairs of dict argument 
        for key, value in dict_obj.items(): 
            print(key,value)
    if __name__ == '__main__':
        nested_dict_pairs_iterator(vehicle_registration)
except Exception as ex:
    print(ex)
